title: mini mexican pizzas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl; stir well and set aside.
Arrange tortillas on baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 2 minutes.
Turn over tortillas; bake an additional minute.
Spread 1/4 cup beans over each tortilla; top with 1/3 cup tomato mixture and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes, or until the tortillas are crisp and cheese melts.
Cut into wedges. Yields 6 servings.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan until it reaches the firm ball stage.
Pour hot syrup over beaten egg whites.
Beat until candy will not adhere to finger when gently touched.
Pour in a greased pan.
Cut into squares or drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: raisin snacks
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in large pan; stir constantly. Remove from heat and add cereal, raisins and peanuts; stir until well coated.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: harvest cake(in honor of james wilson)
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beans.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Add apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan or dish and bake at 375°
(I prefer 350°) for 45 minutes (more or less), or until tests done.
Remove from oven and cool and frost with a cream cheese icing.

title: crab cakes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine egg, the 1/4 cup bread crumbs, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper.
Stir in the crabmeat, carrot and green onion.
Cover and chill for 45 to 60 minutes.

Shape crab mixture into eight 1/4-inch thick patties. Using a spatula to transfer patties, coat patties with the 1/3 cup bread crumbs. In a large skillet, cook crab cakes in oil over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes per side, or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in oil; add soup, broth and green chilies.
Add chicken pieces.
Mix well.
Alternate tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese in layers in large baking pan.
Repeat layers until casserole is filled.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: apricot fried pies
directions: Rinse apricots in cold water.
Place in pan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add sugar; cook for 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Cut pastry into 5-inch circles.
Put heaping tablespoonful of cooked apricots on crust.
Brush edges with water.
Press edge with fork.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: yummy rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti or pasta of your choice in chicken broth an drain.
Saute onion in oil.
Add other ingredients and heat in heavy boiler until cheese melts.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Heat in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: In a large skillet saute mushrooms and green onions in butter for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add tomato, lemon juice, salt and S&W Cajun sauce; heat to a boil.
Stir in shrimp.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes, or until shrimp turns pink.
Stir frequently.
Boil rice on side, by package directions.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp and spicy cranberry dip
directions: If using shrimp:
Bring
cups
hot water to boiling, then add shrimp and bring to boiling again. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1
to
3 minutes until shrimp turn pink; drain. Place shrimp in ice water to chill quickly.

title: chunk of cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese, mix until well blended.
Once blended add cheese cubes and mix making sure to distribute the cheese chunks evenly.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350 for 1-1 1/2 hours.
Pour off liquid.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Bake brownies according to box directions; cool.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Crush candy bar into small pieces (save a portion for shavings.)
In a trifle dish or large bowl, crumble brownies.
Spread with pudding, sprinkle candy bar, spread with Cool Whip.
Continue layers until final layer is Cool Whip. Use shavings of candy bar to top.
This is a great chocolate dessert and will feed about 12 to 16.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Heat chocolate, 1 tablespoon sugar and the cream in a medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Beat egg yolks slightly.
Slowly stir in chocolate mixture. Blend in vanilla. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar just until stiff peaks form. Fold in chocolate mixture. Pour into souffle cups.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: smooth peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together butter, flour and ground pecans and spread in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar and set aside.
Mix together pudding and cold milk and set aside.
Pour cream cheese mixture over crust. Pour pudding over cream cheese.
Top with 1 carton Cool Whip.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box; set aside. Saute onions and celery in margarine until transparent.
Add turkey and broken up sausage; simmer for 8 minutes.
Add mushrooms; simmer for 2 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add noodles and mix well; spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.
This can be made ahead of time.
Also leftovers can be frozen.

title: crab rounds
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and spread on bread. Broil until golden.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine pineapple (and juice) and sugar and cook over medium heat (stir once) until thick (about 20 minutes).
When cake is done, pierce top.
Pour mix over cake and cool.
Combine pudding mix with milk and blend until thick. Spread over cake.
Beat cream until soft peaks.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until stiff.
Spread over cake. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the egg and the sesame seed.
Form mixture into balls the size of a large walnut and flatten with the palm of your hand.
Brush the top of each cookie with the beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, flour, sugar, salt and water 2 to 3 minutes, until clear.
Add Jell-O.
Cool. Add strawberries.
Let congeal a little.
Pour in crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange pecans on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
To test doneness, shake pie to see if beginning to be thick.
Do not overcook.

title: hamburger chowder
directions: Brown ground beef and onions lightly.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: pink cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together in medium bowl. In another bowl, mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
After Jell-O cools, mix Jell-O and cream cheese mixture together.
Mix in separate bowl the ice cold Milnot; whip until it is stiff and fluffy.
Fold the pink mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate until set.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Note: The secret is in the mixing; have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Cream sugar, butter, vanilla and milk.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls size of a walnut, dipping hands into powdered sugar as you roll balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over low heat.
Dip balls into this mixture, one at a time, holding each with a toothpick. Drop on waxed paper.
Candy is moist inside with a hard coating of chocolate.
It stays fresh for several weeks.
Makes 75.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Pour oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Swish around.
Pour in cake mix, eggs, water, pineapple and half of coconut.
Beat with fork until smooth.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Punch holes in hot cake and pour creme of coconut over top of cake.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip and rest of coconut.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chipped ham) and bring to a boil slowly. Add chipped ham and cook slowly for 5 to 10 minutes.
This makes a lot.
Freeze what is left over for another treat later. The longer it sits, the better the flavor.

title: smoked pork chops with gravy
directions: Fry the smoked pork until it is brown. Set aside.
Fry onion until glossy and then bake with the pork chops until tender.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, gelatin and eggs and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add oil and liquid. Beat additional 2 minutes. Fold raspberries into mix. Pour into Bundt or greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: venison sausage ball
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown well in butter, stirring occasionally. Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Arrange on serving dish.

title: buffalo chili
directions: Brown meat first. Add spices and sear with meat. Add chopped onion. Add remaining ingredients except beans and simmer 30 minutes. Add beans and cover to simmer. Makes 12 servings.

title: country fried chuck
directions: Combine the ground chuck, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper and 3/4 cup flour and mix well.
Roll out on floured board about 1/2-inch thick and cut in 4-inch squares.
Place in hot fat in a skillet and cook until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
I use frozen regular pie crust; do not cook first.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar together. Add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, then add milk, a little at a time, ending with flour. Cook in tube pan 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pudding bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat all ingredients 4 minutes. Bakes 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: gerry's nannie's noodle pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cream cheese, cut in pieces and mix well.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Add sour cream; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add cooked noodles, then milk.
Batter will be very watery.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with butter or margarine. Pour in batter.
Take a fork and stir noodles to even the distribution.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients and drizzle on hot cake.

title: creamed baked veal
directions: Melt butter and fry veal in it for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring when necessary.
Uncover and finish browning.
Add flour to fat and meat in skillet and blend well.
Add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add green peppers, salt and pepper and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Add chow mein noodles on top and bake about 15 minutes longer.
Yields 6 medium servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Add the margarine to the potatoes and mix. Add the cream cheese, sour cream and onion.
Add separately and mix after each item.
Put in greased baking dish. Garnish top with paprika and/or Parmesan cheese. Casserole is best if made ahead of time and let cool before baking.
Can be made the day before. Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberried chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, onion soup mix and Italian dressing in a large baking pan.
Marinate chicken in this for several hours. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.
Freezes well.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain fruit well. Mix pudding and milk. Add all ingredients together. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 3 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Top with chopped nuts (1 cup).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Take out and turn out onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll like a log.
Let cool.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Add corn last.
Stir only enough to mix ingredients.
Fry by spoonfuls in deep fat until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 14 to 16 fritters.

title: the french whitehouse veal
directions: Dice bacon and saute until crisp in a heavy, large frypan. Remove bacon bits and save.
Cut veal into 1-inch cubes.
In frypan brown veal on all sides.
Remove veal and save.
Add shallots and garlic and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add flour, cook and stir for 1 minute.
Return veal to pan, stir in chicken broth and 1 1/2 cups wine, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce; simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and cheese well.
Stir in 1 package of taco seasoning.
Brown ground beef, drain grease and add other package of taco seasoning.
Layer as follows:
cheese mixture, ground beef, lettuce, tomatoes, shredded cheese and taco sauce.
Top with black olives if desired.
Serve with taco chips.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Cook until tender and add salt, pepper and oregano.
Combine soup, water, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and 2 dashes of lemon pepper in a separate bowl and mix well.
Place a layer of cooked noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, add a layer of meat mixture and repeat.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: leftover casserole
directions: Combine all together and heat either on top of stove or pour in baking pan.
Top with bread crumbs or crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; form into loaf and lay strips of bacon on top.
Pour catsup on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thick and clear.
Add jello and food coloring.
Add strawberries.
Pour over the sugar mixture in baked pie shell.
Cool.
Let set in refrigerator. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: basque potato pie
directions: Pare potatoes and slice crosswise as thinly as possible.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add salt, if desired.
Toss potatoes in butter; coat evenly.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch plate with potato slices, reserving 8 for garnish.
Brown beef and onion in skillet, breaking meat up with fork as it cooks.
Stir in tomato sauce, cheese and olives, mixing well. Spoon mixture into potato lined pie shell.
Garnish with reserved potato slices. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are soft and edges are lightly browned. Allow pie to stand 5 minutes.

title: brown beef in beer
directions: Dredge meat with flour and brown in 4 tablespoons butter; add parsley, thyme, bay leaf, salt, pepper, vinegar and beer to cover. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour adding more beer if necessary.
Saute sliced onions in 4 tablespoons butter; add sugar and cook until onions are slightly glazed.
Add the onions to beef and cook 15 minutes more or until meat is tender.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Bring to boil.
Cool.
Add juices and mashed bananas; stir well into juices.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer.
When slightly thawed, scrape or mash and put in punch bowl.
Add enough 7-Up to make a slushy punch.
Makes 60 servings.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: spicy honey mustard sauce
directions: Combine the mustard, honey, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in a medium bowl; stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls on cookie sheet.
Bake until browned.

title: crab dip appetizer
directions: Mix
cream cheese, onion, horseradish sauce, mayonnaise and lemon
juice and spread in bottom of dish.
Top with chili sauce, then
sprinkle crab meat
on
top.
Chill and serve on crackers.

title: mulled cranberry drink
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients; slowly bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove from heat; pour juice mixture through strainer to remove whole spices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Mix cake mix, Mandarin oranges with juice, eggs and Crisco.
Beat on medium about 3 minutes.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: easy fruit cake no. 2
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour tube pan well.
Sift together flour and baking soda and set aside.

title: two-squash casserole
directions: Cook yellow squash and zucchini separately in a small amount of boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain well.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend and beat with mixer 2 minutes.
Measure 1 1/2 cups batter into bowl.
Add chocolate syrup and mix well.
Spoon batters alternately into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan on rack 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: lemonly light cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine grape juice, sugar and lemon juice. Stir until sugar dissolves. Chill before serving. Add club soda, fruit and ice. Makes 7 cups.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until well done.
Add tomato soup, 1 can soup water, tomato paste, 1 can water and tomatoes.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 stick butter to the cooked and drained macaroni.
Combine with tomato mixture and pour into greased baking dish.
Top with 3 to 4 slices of bacon (optional).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy saucepan.
Drain.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes, stir occasionally.

title: texas short cake
directions: In large bowl, put sugar, salt and flour, stir.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Heat 2 cups of milk in microwave for about 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Add 6 beaten eggs to flour mixture, then gradually pour in milk.
Put on stove on medium-high and stir until thick or begins to stick.
Take off and add 1 can sweetened condensed milk, 2 cans Pet milk, whipped cream and vanilla.
Add milk to line in freezer.
Takes 20 to 30 minutes in electric ice cream freezer.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham in large baking dish.
With knife, cut crisscross shapes across top and sides.
Inside each cut crisscross, place a whole clove.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well. Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peach delight
directions: Spread over cooled crust.
Slice 4 or 5 medium size peaches; sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.
Place on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato candy
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter, and salt in large pot; cook over medium heat to soft ball stage. Remove from heat and allow to cool until hand can be held comfortably on bottom of pot. Add sweet potatoes and beat until mixture loses it's gloss. Add pecans; mix well and pour into buttered pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix pickle juice and mayonnaise to taste.
Punch holes in salad.
Pour pickle juice mixture on top and let it run through salad.
Sprinkle cornbread on top and serve.

title: indian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix oil or melted lard, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Add flour and water, a little at a time. Knead until dough is very smooth.
Shape in ball and let rise. Cover with cloth in large greased bowl until doubled.
Punch down dough and knead on floured board for at least 5 minutes.
Shape into 4 balls.
Place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise for 20 to 30 minutes in warm place.
Bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Use broom straw or toothpick.

title: carrot relish cups
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat smooth with a beater.
Stir in orange juice, lemon peel and juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add carrots and apples. Spoon into 6 or 8 individual molds or one large mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: 3 minute rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Marinate pork chops 1 hour in marinade of remaining ingredients, except water. Drain chops, reserving marinade.
Wipe dry and brown chops in a greased skillet.
Heat marinade with water and pour around chops in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: muffin breakfast
directions: Divide corn muffin mix in muffin tins.
In other muffin tin, put corned beef hash in bottom and top with egg.
Bake all as directed for muffins.

title: hershey's syrup cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix milk and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients, flour, baking powder and salt; beat until smooth.
Heat oil to frying stage.
Pour batter into a funnel.
Cover bottom of funnel with finger.
Pour only half of the batter in a funnel.
Remove finger, releasing batter into hot oil.
Whirl around, making a round design in the oil.
Cook about 3 minutes and turn over.
Cook on other side.
Drain on a paper towel; sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle topping over the casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Remove skin from the chicken.
Rinse chicken.
In a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven, combine the chicken pieces, the 2 1/2 cups water, onion, bouillon granules, poultry seasoning (or sage or thyme) and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add the carrots and celery.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes more.

title: snack crackers
directions: Place all ingredients in a double brown paper bag.
Pour oil over.
Shake vigorously until mixed.
Store in closed containers. Great in tomato soup!

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: apple pie pizza
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water on top. Shape into ball.
Roll into 15-inch circle on floured surface. Place on 13-inch pizza pan.
Turn up edge to form rim.
Combine Cremora powder, brown sugar, sugar, 1/3 cup flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Sprinkle half of mixture over pastry.
Cut butter into remaining half until crumbly; set aside.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, pork, rice, salt and pepper. Stuff cabbage leaves. Put in large roaster. Cover with lean bacon strips. Heat tomato juice and flour until thick. Pour over rolls. Bake at 350 degrees for two hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place steak in crock-pot. Add bell pepper and onion. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add dry gravy mix.
Pour stewed tomatoes over all. Cook for about 6 hours until steak is tender. Stir once or twice. When done, remove steak. Thicken gravy. Serve with mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: holiday wrappings(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop beef finely with food chopper. Combine all ingredients (except wonton wrappers) in batter bowl. Blend until smooth using super scraper.
Separate wonton wrappers and place one in each cup of the mini muffin pan.
Press each wrapper into cup.
With the small stainless steel scoop, fill cups with cheese mixture.
Wet fingers slightly and pinch top of each wonton wrapper together.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 24 servings.

title: baked rice
directions: In a skillet, melt oleo and brown rice and onion.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, add bouillon and water to rice mixture. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: failproof fudge
directions: Blend egg, confectioners sugar, condensed milk, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Add to the sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square dish.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: black olive dip
directions: Mix ingredients and add reserved olive liquid until desired consistency.
Refrigerate.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: melt away cheese rounds
directions: Cream butter in food processor or mixer until light and fluffy.
Add
cheese,
flour,
salt, paprika or poppy seed and form into
a
dough.
Chill
dough about 2 hours.
Shape dough into small	even balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with some extra paprika or poppy seed.
Bake balls at 400° for about 10
minutes or until just baked through.
The rounds should never get
brown.
Cool and remove carefully.
Store in airtight container.	These rounds may be frozen for later use. Chill the rounds
30	minutes
on
the
baking
sheets
before baking.

title: minerva beer sours
directions: Combine.
Pour over ice and watch out!

title: rice casserole
directions: Stir.
Cook in oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken florentine(microwave)
directions: With flat side of meat mallet, pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place ham slice, cheese slice and 1/4 of the spinach on each chicken piece.
Rol up chicken from short end, jelly roll fashion.
Secure with wooden toothpicks, if needed. Place chicken, seam side down, in a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish. Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add pumpkin.
Add oil, beat and add vanilla.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins, mixing well.
Pour into large loaf pan, greased and floured or makes 3 layer cake.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cherry salad
directions: Combine
cherries
and sugar and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let cool.
Mix cheese, pineapple and nuts. Add to cooled mixture in pan.
Mix and congeal.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bar in microwave; mix with Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook beef and pork until tender.
Grind with food chopper. Cook raisins and currants until soft.
Chop citron, apples, oranges and lemons very fine.
Add meat with other ingredients and simmer together for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while hot. Makes approximately 7 quarts.

title: seafood spread
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; mix well, adding Old Bay to your taste.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana-oatmeal bars
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into bowl.
Add shortening, egg, bananas, oats and nuts.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Spread into 10 x 15-inch greased cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly.

title: tuna salad
directions: Gently blend all ingredients.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks and mix well.
Sift flour and soda together; add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Start cooking at 300° and cook for 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes, increase heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 13 x 9-inch pan, two 8-inch rounds or Bundt pan.

title: cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to fruit.
Mix fruit/flour mixture with butter and sugar mixture. Add pecans. Bake in tube pan for 3 hours at 250°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk; beat well. Combine this with raisins and uncooked oatmeal.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: surprise puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in microwave or on stove-top. Open crescent rolls and separate into triangles. Dip a marshmallow and roll in the cinnamon/sugar.
Place marshmallow at the wide end of the triangle and roll the dough around the marshmallow. Be sure to seal the dough around the marshmallow completely to avoid leaks.
Place the dough in a muffin tin and repeat until all the crescent rolls are used. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: squash fritters
directions: Stir everything together good.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into 1/4 inch oil in skillet.
Turn over to brown on both sides.

title: peas and rice
directions: In saucepan, brown rice with sage and butter.
Add broth. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add peas.
Simmer 10 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally. Makes 3 cups.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, pineapple and coconut; mix well.
In a 2-quart bowl, layer bananas and grapes and half of the cheese mixture.
Then layer peaches and pear slices and remaining cheese mixture.
Top with strawberries.
Chill and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients. Spread mayonnaise on top, then sprinkle chopped bacon next. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sesame chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size cubes.
Stir with salad oil, soy sauce, wine, egg whites and ginger.
Marinate 1 hour.
Combine bread crumbs and sesame seed; roll chicken cubes in this mixture or shake in a closed plastic bag.
Arrange in a single layer on a shallow nonstick baking pan sprayed with cooking spray.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken, cut up and add soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Put in baking dish; melt butter, mix with cracker crumbs and poppy seed. Put on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Beat oil and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water and blend in 1 package of cream cheese.
This mixture should be filled with tiny lumps.
Add the cold water and relish.

title: scalloped corn and tomatoes
directions: Mix corn, peppers, cream, sugar, salt, butter and tomatoes. Put in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: shish kabobs
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the first 6 ingredients to make marinade.
Cut steak into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place steak and marinade sauce in pan. Refrigerate for 8 hours. Stir occasionally. You will need 12 skewers.
Place meat and vegetables (quartered) on the skewers.
Broil on grill for 15 to 20 minutes. Brush on your marinade over kabobs while cooking.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, onion, milk, bread crumbs, egg and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Shape into a ball and place in the center of a baking pan.
Combine ketchup and brown sugar and pour over the meat loaf.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large heavy pan place confectioner's sugar, butter, and evaporated milk.
Cook over med. heat stirring constantly until all ingredients melt.
Continue cooking to 235° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in marshmallow creme and peanut butter.
Stir well and pour into 2 8x8x2 inch buttered pans.
When cold, cut into squares. Makes about 6 lbs. of fudge.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse spaghetti.
Stir in the dressings, onion, celery and green pepper.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: corn roasted in foil(2 ears each)
directions: Combine water and sugar in a large roasting pan.
Add corn and soak for 15 minutes.
Remove from water and wrap each ear, still in its husks, in a piece of aluminum foil.
Twist ends to close. Place wrapped corn on grill, 5 inches from heat, and roast for 15 to 20 minutes, turning often.

title: caramel macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cook the nuts on a cookie sheet at 350° until slightly brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Mix butter and sugar; add next 3 ingredients. Stir well, then mix in flour and nuts.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dried onion and mustard together.
Add parsley flakes and frozen crab.
Serve on a Triscuit.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in 8 cup glass measure or bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave 2 to 6 minutes or until syrup and peanuts are light brown, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and then baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Working quickly, spread 1/4 inch thick on buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand until cool, 40 to 60 minutes.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container in a cool place.

title: shrimp dip 2
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese until smooth. Add Worcestershire sauce to taste, usually to a light tan/beige color. Then add minced onions and garlic powder. Spread mixture into a concave dish (dish with a lip on it, not a flat plate). Gently spread about 3/4 of the cocktail sauce on top of cheese mixture. Leave a 1/2-inch of cheese mixture showing around the edge. Crumble (well dried) shrimp on top of cocktail sauce. Chill for 3 to 4 hours. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges and save juices.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until brown.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Pour glaze over bread while still hot in pans.
Leave in pans about 1 hour.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread 1 cup of mixture onto crust, spread evenly. Top with 1/3
cup fat free caramel topping and 1/4 cup toasted pecans. Top with remaining cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate 3 hours. Garnish with additional caramel topping and pecans.

title: venison
directions: Remove all fat and bone from venison meat.
Thinly slice meat and place in large bowl.
Add Worcestershire sauce to coat all meat for marinating.
Add finely chopped onions, garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Keep covered.
Stir every few hours.

title: chicken with wine
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with "Pam spray."
Put chicken in pan.
Cover chicken with cheese slices.
Mix broth and wine and pour over cheese.
Partially crush croutons and spread over top. Drizzle with margarine.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Delicious nice company dish!

title: english marmalade
directions: Cut fruit very finely, including the rinds.
To every quart of pulp, add 1 1/2 quarts of boiling water.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: hot cocoa cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large mixing bowl and set aside. Combine margarine, oil, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Mix and beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Mix well and bake in pan at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cover with icing.

title: pumpkin whoopie cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs to mixture.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and nuts.
Mix dry ingredients with banana mixture.
Pour in loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: tofu lasagne
directions: Combine minced garlic, undrained tomatoes, tomato paste and sweet basil in small saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes to make sauce.
Set aside.

title: skewered chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips, 1 1/4-inches wide and 1/4-inch thick. Thread strips loosely into 6 to 8 skewers.
Place skewers in 2 layers in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours; drain.
Grill over hot coals 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken canneloni
directions: Boil chicken breast and then shred very fine.
Mix chicken, Italian seasoning, parsley, garlic, basil and oregano.
Heat and add egg, bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese. Stir well and set aside.

title: western casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix together beef, corn, beans, soup, cheese, onion and chili powder.
Bake, uncovered, in a hot oven (400°) until hot, about 20 minutes.
Dip biscuits in butter, then in corn meal.
Place around edge of casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer until biscuits are golden brown.

title: low cholesterol cookie
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Stir into oats. Beat egg whites with a fork and then combine with sugar, oil, milk, vanilla and raisins.
Lastly, combine with flour mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.
Shorter baking time makes for a chewy cookie.
Bake longer and they are crisp.

title: waldorf aster cake
directions: Have all measures level.
Add mayonnaise and sugar; cream. Sift cocoa and flour together; add to mayonnaise and sugar mixture.
Add baking soda; mix.
Last, add water and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: melon ball
directions: Serve as a shot or over ice.

title: cream cheese danish(won second place in the agency dessert contest pastries category)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the cream cheese until smooth in a mixer or food processor.
Add sugar and egg yolk to mixture; blend until smooth.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; blend.
Spread 1 package of crescent rolls in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour cream cheese mixture over rolls on top.
Spread the remaining package of rolls on top.
Mix the egg white with teaspoon of water; brush over the tops of the rolls.
Bake for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken adobo(philippine breast of chicken)
directions: Brown chicken.
Combine ingredients and pour over chicken. Cook for about 30 minutes.
Take chicken out of broth.
Put 1 teaspoon of cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Mix.
Then stir in broth.
Heat until thickened.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown and crumble sausage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Do not peel rhubarb.
Cut into 1-inch chunks.
Boil sugar, rhubarb and water for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple; boil for 10 more minutes.
Add jello; cook for 7 minutes.
Take off heat.
Skim, ladle into jars and seal.

title: consomme rice
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Melt oleo; brown rice and onion lightly. (Rice should get almost brown before adding onion.)
Put in casserole and add consomme.
Cover lightly and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dates with soda and boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Mix baking powder with flour.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Bake in a 9-inch loaf pan, well-greased, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookiesspringfield, missouri
directions: Mix flour with soda; combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water; add drained pineapple juice.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water.
Pour into hot gelatin mix and stir.
Add sugar.
While cooling, grind cranberries, grind orange, chop celery and pecans; stir into gelatin mix, along with crushed pineapple.
Chill until mixture sets.
Can be molded or put into a serving dish.

title: shrimp and cottage cheese salad
directions: Cut shrimp into bite size pieces.
In a medium bowl, mix together shrimp and other ingredients and chill until serving time. When ready to serve, heap shrimp mixture on lettuce cups.
Garnish with tomato wedges and parsley sprigs.
Makes 4 main course servings.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut hot dogs in fourths.
Cut bacon strips in thirds.
Wrap bacon strip around hot dog piece.
Cover all with brown sugar. Bake in jelly roll pan (with sides) or in Pyrex dish with sides. Bake 1 hour at 350°; drain.
Makes 40 (9 x 13-inch "makes" 64.)

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Put remaining cheese on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: noodles and ham
directions: Saute diced ham in butter until slightly crisp. Cook noodles in salted boiling water until done.
On a hot platter, mix noodles with ham and drippings.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: dipping plum sauce for ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mustard, in blender.
Add mustard, a little at a time, blending well, until sauce is as hot and spicy as desired.
(Longer blending makes hotter sauce.) Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: mary's green rice
directions: Saute onion and rice in margarine in skillet until brown. Stir in salt and water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Add 2 cups of boiling water to jello.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Add all of the other ingredients, except the sour cream. Pour half of the mixture into a dish and let chill.
Next, spread sour cream on first half of mixture.
Next, spread second half of jello mixture onto the sour cream.
Congeal
until firm.
May be prepared day before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers) together.
Chill in refrigerator. Serve on crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and soups to make a sauce. Alternate layers of tortillas, chicken, sauce and grated cheese. Bake in moderate oven until hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Add cornstarch to sugar.
Add water and salt to dry mixture. Boil over medium heat until mixture bubbles clear.
Remove from heat.
Add jello, stir and let cool.
Clean fresh strawberries and mix with glaze and pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Add whipped topping before serving, if desired.

title: zucchini beef skillet
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
A good summer recipe.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter and stir in onions.
Fry until onion is translucent.
Add 1/2 stick butter and 1 tablespoon flour.
Mix well.
Add half and half, a little at a time, alternating with water.
Mix in clams with juice.
Bring to boil.
Add potatoes. Add celery.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add flour to thicken, if desired.
Bring to a boil until vegetables are tender.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Mix ingredients (except ginger ale).
Sweeten to taste.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.

title: chicken and rice parmesan
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of greased 3-quart casserole.
Mix together soups.
Pour 3/4 of mixture over rice.
Stir until well mixed.
Place chicken over rice.
Cut butter into chunks.
Place on chicken.
Cover with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add other ingredients. Simmer until thick.
This is good cooked in a crock-pot.
We fix it for reunion dinners.
It's great with Mexican cornbread and slaw.
Easy and delicious!

title: cranberry salad - congealed #2
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Let cool. Stir in cranberry sauce. Add nuts and crushed pineapple. Pour into mold or dish and refrigerate.

title: my mother-in-laws italian spaghetti
directions: Brown the sausage.
Take
the sausage out of the casing and crumble
with
a fork (or leave as chunks) while cooking. Drain fat
from the sausage.
Add the tomato puree, sauce and paste. Bring
to a boil and simmer for 4 to 5 hours, stirring frequently. If you don't have time to stay at home all day to cook and
stir it, put it on low in a crock-pot, but leave the lid
partway off so the moisture can escape. The sauce is very thick and delicious.

title: zucchini with poppy seed
directions: Saute the onion in oil in a covered heavy saucepan over low heat for 20 minutes.
Do not allow the onion to brown.
Add the salt, paprika, almost all the poppy seed and pepper to taste.
Trim off the ends of the zucchini and cut them into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
If the vegetable has drawn much water, uncover and cook rapidly for a few minutes to evaporate the excess liquid.
Transfer the zucchini to a serving dish, spoon the sour cream on top and sprinkle with the remaining poppy seed.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers.
Mix French vanilla instant pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat 2 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, then the rest of the pudding mixture.
Top with crackers.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Soak onions in hot water until soft, drain.
Mix sauce, poppy seeds, mustard and onions together.
Melt margarine and brush on inside of split rolls.
Spread poppy seed mixture on inside of rolls.
Add ham and cheese.
Put tops on rolls and brush margarine. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, one cup at a time, beating until smooth. Add 7-Up and flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, keeping door closed all during time of cooking.

title: marie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion, Italian seasoning, garlic, salt, pepper and parsley in ground meat.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water and sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk; let come to a rolling boil. Let boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts. Stir quickly until smooth. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Let cool before cutting.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and extracts.
Beat egg yolks.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add into the mixture.
Beat egg whites and mix into batter.
Add 1/3 cup brandy.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Temperature can be raised to 300°.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Remove each roll from aluminum tray.
Dip into melted margarine or butter, coating entire roll.
Place each roll into bag containing the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Shake the mixture onto the rolls (I do 3 or 4 at once).
Remove from bag.
Place in aluminum tray.
When all rolls have been coated with mixture, bake at 350° until warm, approximately 5 minutes.
Watch closely, they burn easily.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt onto a piece of waxed paper.
To dry ingredients add eggs and milk in a bowl and beat lightly.
Stir in oil and corn.
Heat oil to 375°.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil and fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: mama rose's french toast
directions: In pie plate or shallow mixing bowl, whisk egg, then add milk, whisking until well combined.
Add vanilla and cinnamon, whisking again or mix with fork.
Preheat skillet over medium heat, melting butter.
Dip bread on both sides in egg mixture, then brown on both sides in hot skillet, turning only once, adding butter as skillet dries with additional bread slices until mixture is gone.
Sprinkle with sugar or serve with honey or favorite syrup.

title: angel food cake with diet icing
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool 2 hours or you can cool quickly with a fan.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together and add to the mixture.
Blend in pineapple and vanilla.
If batter seems too stiff, add a little pineapple juice.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice with cooked
and drained broccoli.
Add chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Top with
bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream peanut butter until well blended.
Add sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Lower heat to 300° and bake 15 minutes more.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: panetone(fruited italian bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, 2 eggs, butter and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in fruit, anise seed, nuts and enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough into lightly floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch dough down; divide in half.
Shape each half into round, slightly half loaf.
Place loaves in opposite corners of greased baking sheet.
Cut a cross 1/2-inch deep on top of each loaf.
Let rise until doubled about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Blend 1 egg and 1 tablespoon water. Brush over loaves.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: Rinse, dry and hull strawberries.
If they are large, cut them in half.
Set aside.
In a deep, medium size saucepan over medium heat, combine red wine, orange juice and honey with 3 cups of water and bring the liquid to a simmer.
Remove the pan from heat and add the strawberries.
Allow to cool.
In a blender, puree the strawberries and liquid in batches until smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl and chill.
If desired, just before serving, beat sour cream until slightly thinned and use to garnish soup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: maple custard(diabetic dessert)
directions: Beat eggs with maple syrup, flavoring and salt until foamy and well blended.
Gradually beat milk into egg mixture.
Transfer into 6 custard cups.
Place cups into a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Custard is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: abby's famous pecan pie
directions: Cool; pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Top with Meringue.

title: zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle salt on zucchini in small bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Squeeze dry with paper towel.
Wipe out bowl and return zucchini to bowl.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella, 1/2 cup of the Cheddar, the Romano and the eggs.
Press the mixture evenly into the bottom of the pan. Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown beef with onion about 5 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, garlic and oregano.
Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Spoon sauce over zucchini crust.
Sprinkle with green pepper, mushroom and the remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from Bing cherries and pineapple to make 2 cups. Bring to a boil and pour over Jell-O.
Mix well and cool.
Use part of gelatin mixture to blend with cream cheese in blender. Mix with other gelatin.
Add Coke.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Use to baste chicken, beef ribs or pork ribs.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix the above ingredients and chill.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Wash and seed peppers.
Pack sliced peppers in jar.
Add 1 teaspoon salt per pint.
Pour boiling water over peppers and let set overnight.
Drain and rinse well.
Bring to boil vinegar and sugar.
Pour over peppers and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 10 minutes as directed on package.
Mix with next 6 ingredients as listed.
Pour into casserole; dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar; add 1 egg at a time.
Alternate dry mixture and milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in Bundt or angel food pan.

title: pineapple milk shake
directions: Blend in blender all ingredients until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: coquille st. jacques
directions: In a medium pan, cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter. Add scallops, lemon juice, salt, paprika, wine and marjoram; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and simmer 2 more minutes. Drain liquid into container and set aside.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray cake pan with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° until the cake springs back in a tube pan.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Cube and slice off crusts of bread.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage; drain and lay over bread.
Shred cheese and sprinkle over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into small pieces.
Saute celery and onion.
Cook in butter.
Add Pet cream, green chili, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Add chicken; cook 10 minutes.
Cool.
Put tortillas in chicken broth.
Cut chicken in small pieces.
Add mild Cheddar cheese.
Layer in casserole dish corn tortillas; cut in small pieces.
Put chicken mixture over the tortillas.
Top with cheese over the tortillas.
Bake 35 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stained window glass cookies
directions: In large bowl mix the chocolate chips and margarine with colored marshmallows and chopped nuts.
On wax paper sprinkle some coconut.
Pour mixture on wax paper and form into a roll.
Place in refrigerator to harden, then slice into pieces.
This will keep 3 to 4 months.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add flour, a little at a time, adding 1 egg at a time.
Start in cold oven. Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones.
Cut in pieces.
Blend soup and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion over medium-high heat.
Drain excess fat.

title: new york style sour cream cheesecake
directions: Mix both cheeses together.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla and margarine and mix in.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° on middle rack of oven for 1 hour.
Shut off oven and leave cheesecake in for 2 more hours.
Top with canned fruit topping and serve.

title: texas beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together until thick.
Cook in slow cooker until done.

title: weight watchers "curb the urge" salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
This will keep crisp several days, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: confetti spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook beef, green pepper and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, brown sugar, salt, chili powder, pepper, garlic powder and cayenne pepper. Drain spaghetti; add to the beef mixture. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: grandma's chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Measure flour, cocoa and spices, salt and soda; set aside. Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, vanilla and applesauce.
Mix well.
Pour cake into tube pan, greased and lined with wax paper.
Cake can be baked in any pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit and cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 2 hours.

title: salmonettes
directions: After the rabbit has been cleaned and soaked in salt water, cut off front and back legs.
Cut back in two pieces.
Wash and soak again in salt water.
Salt and flour; put in skillet where cooking oil has been added.
Brown rabbit on both sides, turning often. Pour little water in skillet and cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly
blend
graham
cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press firmly against bottom and 2 1/2 inches up sides of
an
8-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add
cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend
in
sour cream.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350°
for 60
minutes.
Turn
off
oven, leaving door slightly ajar.
Allow cheese cake to remain in oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Chill
4 hours
or
overnight.
Remove side of pan.
Top with pie filling. Makes 10 wedges.

title: mother's squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook squash and onions in boiling saltwater for 5 minutes; drain. Combine chicken soup and sour cream; stir in shredded carrots. Fold in squash and onions. Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Spread half of stuffing mixture on the bottom of a baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture on top of stuffing. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until soft. Let cool with skins on. When cool, peel and dice into large chunks. Peel and dice onion and add to potatoes. Add corned beef. Chop with metal spatula until all ingredients are mixed well. Fry until onions are soft and serve. This recipe is for 4 people.

title: ham delights
directions: Heat margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on top and bottom of sliced rolls.
Add ham and cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and nuts.
Mix together the eggs, soup, soup mix, milk and mayonnaise.
Add mix to broccoli and nuts.
Sprinkle cheese on top first, then the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Better if you make ahead and let set in refrigerator before cooking.
(May use Ritz crackers instead of bread crumbs.)

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados; remove pits and reserve one pit.
Mash pulp with fork.
Add lime juice, tomato, onion and salt.
Add picante sauce, if desired.
Mix well.
Place avocado pit on top of guacamole.
Cover and refrigerate; remove pit when ready to serve. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: tasty cakes
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add flour and milk. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. While cake is still hot, spread on peanut butter; refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate with 1/2 teaspoon of oil; spread on top of peanut butter.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: helen's salad dressing
directions: Mix in equal proportions.
Add extra honey or vinegar to suit taste.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, peppers.
Mix sugar, spice, vinegar. Bring syrup to a boil and add the ground mixture.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put in pint jars.
Seal.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan and cook, stirring constantly.
Cranberries will pop as they cook.
Should be slightly thick.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use 1 or 2 tablespoons of mix to 1 cup of hot water.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate wings overnight for 12 to 24 hours.
Cook, covered with foil, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, then remove foil and cook another 15 minutes or until done.
Great for family gatherings!

title: grandma biz's hot dish
directions: Brown onion and celery until done. Add hamburger and fry until done. Cook egg noodles; drain with cold water. Put hamburger, noodles, corn and soup in casserole dish. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together.
Heat juice from pears. Add jello and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: french fries
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Put cooking oil in pan and heat. Place potatoes in pan and cook until light brown.
Drain; put potatoes in bowl and add salt and eat.

title: simple pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles until tender; drain and pour into large salad bowl.
Microwave vegetables for 5 minutes until tender; drain and pour on top of noodles.
Mix well with large plastic spoon in order not to tear up noodles.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and dressing; toss until well mixed.
Ready to eat.
Add diced meat if desired.
Pepper and salt to desired taste.

title: unleavened bread keeps like hardtack
directions: Mix with water to a stiff dough and knead and pull until lively.
Roll like soda crackers and score with a knife.

title: peanut soup
directions: (If you do not like onion chunks in soup, grind up in blender with milk.
Otherwise add milk to broth.)

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan.
Dump pineapple in pan and spread.
Dump in pie filling and spread.
Dump cake mix in and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Put butter slices on and bake at 350° for 48-53 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie(refrigerated)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks slightly and combine with milk, brown sugar, pumpkin, salt and spices.
Cook over low heat or in double boiler and stir constantly until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is almost set, then beat until light and fluffy.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add granulated sugar gradually and beat until mixture forms soft, moist peaks.
Fold into pumpkin mixture and pour into pie shell.
Chill until set or overnight.

title: charlotte's buns
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Spread mixture on hamburger buns or Italian rolls.
Add a layer of ham and Swiss cheese.
Wrap sandwiches in foil and freeze.
Remove from freezer several hours before serving.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Fry hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Cook macaroni.
Add all ingredients.
Cut tomatoes in bite size pieces.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in lightly oiled skillet.
Add chopped vegetables. Stir-fry about 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste, soup, tomatoes and liquid.
Cook, stirring frequently, in covered skillet or pan 30 to 45 minutes.
Add dark red kidney beans last after washing and draining well.
Add water, if necessary, for desired consistency. Add cayenne pepper, cautiously, if desired.
Reheat just before serving.
Serve with cooked rice and saltines.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 pie shells.
You can use chocolate graham cracker pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: green relish
directions: Mix well and pour in jars and seal.

title: great chicken salad
directions: Mix well and serve with Ritz crackers or in pastry shell.

title: broccoli, potato, cheese soup
directions: Melt the butter and fry onion and celery in it.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Work together crushed pretzels, melted oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes. Let cool.

title: my favorite cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar well.
Add egg, one at a time, beating well.
Add milk and flour alternately; mix well.
Bake 3 or 4 layers.
Use any filling; my favorite is Seven Minute Frosting.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and form into small balls and chill.
Then dip in 1 pound package almond bark, melted in double boiler.
Place on wax paper to set.

title: pudding candy
directions: Cook puddings, sugar and milk for 1 minute over high heat, stirring vigorously for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, marshmallows and vanilla.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet; add onions, garlic and beef. Cook and stir until browned; stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, paprika, mustard, pepper and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cover; simmer 2 hours (I use round steak; it will become tender if simmered for 2 hours).
Blend flour slowly with 1/4 cup water; stir gradually into meat mixture until thickened, 1 minute.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish and bake on low heat until rice appears to be done.
You may want to add some additional water to casserole if it appears to be getting dry in oven.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Beat egg white until creamy.
Slowly add sugar, Crisco and butter.
Beat on high until frosting.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pineapple walnut cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: working for peanuts pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust; sprinkle with peanuts.
Chill 8 hours.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: turkey in the straw
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine.
Combine turkey with soup, milk and mushrooms.
Add sauteed ingredients. Line casserole dish with 1/2 noodles.
Pour mixture over noodles. Add remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion slightly.
Combine with hominy, chilies, sour cream, soup and 1/2 of cheese.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix boxes of jello pudding together.
Add them to 3 cups boiling water and bring mixture to a boil.
Let cool and when it thickens, fold in Dream Whip and oranges (drain the juice first). Chill in refrigerator.

title: burgoo
directions: Cover and simmer chicken, beef, onion, salt, pepper and water in large heavy kettle until chicken falls off bones. Cut chicken in pieces and return to kettle. Add tomato sauce, vegetables, rice and sauce.
Cover and simmer two hours or longer.
During last half hour, add butter and crumbs.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Boil kielbasa in water with vinegar for 5 minutes. In a greased deep dish, layer onions, potatoes and bell pepper.
Also salt and pepper to taste. Add 1/2 cup water. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Lay kielbasa on top and cover tightly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: In heavy skillet, heat Wesson oil.
Add garlic and onion and cook until soft.
Add beef and seasonings; cook until crumbly. Mix in tomato paste and hot water; simmer 5 minutes.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, place a thin layer of sauce, next put half the noodles, then all the Ricotta or cottage cheese and on top of that, half the Mozzarella.
Repeat with the remaining half of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand out of oven for 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large bowl, break up tuna fish.
Add tomatoes, onion and pasta.
Mix well.
Add cucumber dressing and mix again.
Add mayonnaise to make very creamy.
Put mixture in casserole dish and cover top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Peel cooked potatoes.
Brown bacon and break or cut into pieces.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Cube cheese; mix together. Cook in crock-pot 2 to 4 hours on low.

title: lemon flavored pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in pan.
Cover and bring to boil.
Uncover when it starts to boil.
Beat egg whites.
Test mixture, drop a small amount of mixture in cup of cold water. If drop forms a ball, mixture is ready.
Pour mixture into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Spread mixture on cake.
Add pineapple and coconut.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Layer 1/2 of the bread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Put in all the cream cheese.
Put in the rest of the bread.
Mix beaten eggs, maple syrup, milk, cinnamon sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread, cover with plastic wrap overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup or fruit.
Serves 8.

title: green beans italian
directions: Cook bacon.
Place green beans in water in 1/2-quart microwave-proof casserole.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 9 to 10 minutes, or until almost tender, stirring once during cooking time.
Add onion and Italian dressing.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 3 to 4 minutes, or until beans are tender and onion is transparent.
Sprinkle with crumbled cooked bacon.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger in pan and drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce. Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Place in casserole dish alternating layers of noodles, meat with sauce and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Crumble cake mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling, pineapple, nuts and coconut into order over cake mix. Melt butter.
Pour over all and bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Soak bran in water.
Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Mix milk and eggs.
Add to Crisco and sugar.
Mix in bran mixture.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Gently fold in until moistened the All-Bran.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes in muffin pans.
Store in refrigerator 3 to 4 weeks.

title: beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Place in large bowl.
In large skillet, place shortening, beef and onion.
Drain off excess fat. Add salt, pepper, steak sauce and catsup.
Mix meat and macaroni; let cool.
Add cheese.
Mix egg, milk, 1/2 cup catsup and additional cheese, if desired.
Pour over casserole mixture and bake in covered dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ozark pie
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to apples and nuts. Combine sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir into fruit mixture. Spoon into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set and lightly brown.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy. Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 375° oven until light golden, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to rack (close to each other) and while cookies are still warm, sift heavily with confectioners sugar.
Cool, then store airtight in cool, dry place.
Before serving, sift cookies with more confectioners sugar.
Makes about 48.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Bake potato in oven or microwave until done.
Immediately after taking from oven, slice open potato and remove "meat" of potato.
Place in medium sized bowl.
Mash potato with fork. Gradually mix in powdered sugar.
Add butter while hot.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Shape dough into little potato shapes.
In a small bowl, mix instant cocoa and cinnamon.
Roll mini potatoes in mixture.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wassail bowl
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan over high heat, heat apple cider, cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix these ingredients well and sprinkle over squash mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beach boys punch
directions: Mix 1 quart cranberry juice and juice of 2 lemons with the 1 pint orange juice and place in punch bowl over cake of ice.
Add the 2 quarts of ginger ale.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: jenny's watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can serve immediately or refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry and pear relish
directions: Combine sugar, water and lemon juice in a pan. Bring to a boil, stirring, then simmer for 5 minutes. Add the pears. Boil, then simmer for 5 minutes. Add the cranberries, then bring to a boil for 7 minutes. Remove from heat and add the ground allspice. Let cool and add lemon juice to taste. Transfer to glass bowl and refrigerate.

title: cinnamon glazed ham
directions: Melt butter in saucepan on low heat.
Blend in arrowroot. Remove from heat and add water, mustard, cinnamon, sugar, lemon juice and raisins.
Heat to a boil; stir constantly for 1 minute. Spoon over ham in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: brown rice
directions: Place butter in pan.
Add chopped onion; brown this.
Pour on bouillon and consomme soups.
Add uncooked rice.
Place in casserole; cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pasta with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in a large saute or frypan. Saute nuts, tomatoes, garlic and broccoli (until broccoli is tender but still very green).
Add cooked pasta and toss.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with grated Italian cheese when ready to serve.
Serve at room temperature.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook gizzards in enough water to cover until almost done.
Add livers and cook until tender.
Chop in small pieces.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Add green onions, celery, green pepper and onions.
Cook over low heat until they are soft.
Add parsley flakes, garlic and meats.
Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes, stirring until well blended.
Add thyme, salt, pepper and then rice with broth from gizzards.
Mix well.
Spoon into casserole and bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: quick shrimp curry
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add seasonings; saute 30 seconds.
Add shrimp.
Saute 2 minutes or just until pink.
With slotted spoon, remove shrimp to bowl.
To mixture in skillet, stir in flour, tomato paste and 1/4 cup chicken broth. Gradually stir in remaining chicken broth.
Boil 2 minutes to thicken.
Add shrimp; toss.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour into bowl. Serve over rice.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Wash and cut off flowerets of broccoli.
Place on microwave safe plate.
Dab butter on top.
Salt.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Grate cheese.
Remove plastic wrap and sprinkle cheese on top.
Replace plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Let stand for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green pepper, peas, onion rings and celery. Spread mayonnaise over all ingredients.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Sprinkle with bacon bits when ready to serve.

title: baked lemon and pepper catfish fillets
directions: Place catfish in baking dish.
Melt butter and brush over fillets.
Sprinkle with lemon-pepper seasoning.
For more lemon taste, pour a teaspoonful of lemon juice over each fillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on thickness of fillets.

title: amazing ambrosia pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, orange rind, butter and vanilla in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: oven omelet
directions: Beat eggs and milk by hand; stir in other ingredients.
Pour into buttered 8-inch glass baking dish.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Any kind of meat may be used instead of ham.
Try bacon or crab.
They are both good.
Good any meal.

title: pea cottage cheese soup
directions: In 2-quart
saucepan
combine
potatoes, celery, onion, chicken broth, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes until vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, in blender,
combine
cottage cheese, peas and milk and blend, covered,
until
smooth.
Stir
mixture
into
the cooked vegetables and heat.
Do not allow it to boil.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour, stirring several times during the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cheeses well with seasonings and pecans.
Shape into a ball and wrap in waxed paper and chill.
When well chilled, shape into a firm ball or log.
(May wait to add pecans until ball is firm and roll to cover or roll in chopped parsley, chili powder or sprinkle with paprika for serving.)

title: creamy butter icing
directions: Beat butter and egg yolk until creamy.
Add sugar gradually. Add vanilla; beat well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing and Salad Supreme together.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Add pepper, celery, onion, tomatoes and olives, all chopped fine.
Refrigerate and stir occasionally.

title: ground hog
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Put into crock-pot with cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve warm on crackers.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together as many as 8 times.
Beat whites until stiff and sprinkle in cream of tartar.
Add ingredients, tablespoonful at one time, if using electric mixer. Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes in ungreased tube pan.
Cool cake in pan for 1 hour inverted over a bottle.
Then remove and peel outer layer before frosting.

title: no-guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 9 inch pie plate, mix soup, vegetables, and chicken.

title: lisa's nanny's tea cakes
directions: Sift flour in large bowl; make hole in flour mixture.
Mix together soda, buttermilk and vanilla (be sure soda is dissolved well).
Use electric mixer to cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add buttermilk mixture.
