Gradually pour this into hole in flour and mix well.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and oleo; cream well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, milk, soda and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and coconut.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut kernels off ears of corn to make 1 cup.
Stir together flour, baking powder, and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg, milk, and corn.
Stir in dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Heat 1 1/2 inches oil to 375° in skillet that is a least 3 inches deep. Drop batter by tablespoons into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes per side, turning once.
Drain on paper toweling. Serve with warm maple syrup, if desired.
Makes 24 fritters.

title: applesauce, canned
directions: Wash, pare if desired, quarter and core cooking apples. Simmer, covered, with cinnamon in a small amount of water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon.
Press apples through sieve.
Stir in sugar.
Reheat to boiling.
Pour, boiling hot, into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Stir with rubber bottle scraper or other non-metallic spoon to remove air bubbles. Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 20 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: quick gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients;
refrigerate at least 2 hours, overnight
is
better.
To	serve,	ladle into small bowls and garnish
with sour cream and cucumber slice.
Good to have for a Fourth of July picnic.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook the pasta for about 10 minutes in a huge pot of boiling water.
Meanwhile heat the oil in a large frying pan.
Add the onion, pepper, zucchini, squash, garlic and ginger.
Saute for about 4 minutes or until vegetables are just crisp-tender.
Then add the mushrooms, tomatoes, snow peas, scallions and parsley. Cook for about 3 minutes more.
Drain the pasta; toss it with the vegetables, soy sauce, sesame oil and hot sesame oil.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook meat; drain fat.
Add soup, beans, onion, hot sauce and corn; mix well and cook together for a few minutes.
In large baking dish, put layer of tortillas, layer of mixture, top with cheese and continue these layers until mixture is used and top again with cheese.
Place in oven until cheese is well melted.

title: casserole for brunch
directions: Cube bread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sausage and cheese over bread.
Beat the eggs, milk and mustard together and pour over ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Slice paper thin; also, the onions.
Mix with salt and ice cubes in a plastic bag.
Refrigerate for 3 hours and then drain.
Boil sugar, vinegar, bay leaves, mustard seed and turmeric for 5 minutes.
Add cucumbers and onions.
As soon as it comes to a full boil again, remove from heat and put in jars.
For safekeeping, boil the jars and lids to sterilize them.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: texas apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 5 minutes. Seal in jars or may be refrigerated for up to 1 month in unsealed jar.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger.
Use a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread macaroni on the bottom.
Place hamburger and spaghetti sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add juice, cranberries, celery, apples and nuts.
Pour in mold and place in refrigerator.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in the shortening.
Put the egg in a cup; add enough water to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Pour this over other mixture; mix until forms a smooth ball.
It is then ready to roll out.
This makes three 2-crust pies or six 1-crust pies.
It also keeps well in refrigerator for a week.

title: potato chowder
directions: In pan over medium heat, brown bacon; pour off fat.
Add white and green parts of onions (reserve 1/2 cup of dark tops).
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add broth and potatoes.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add carrots; cook 5 minutes more.
Add bell pepper, zucchini, corn and thyme; cook until tender.
Add turkey or chicken and reserved onion tops.
Mix milk with cornstarch; add to pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: stuffed-sausage mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms; remove stems.
Dice mushrooms; set aside. Place mushroom caps in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Brush mushroom caps with melted butter.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake at 400° in covered dish until rice is tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Toss with lettuce, cheese, onion, tomato and beans.
Stir in dressing and Fritos.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour and 1/4 cup milk.
Mix to form a smooth paste.
Stir into boiling soup.
Add remaining 2 3/4 cups milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and soup thickens.
Eat and enjoy!

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Saute the onion and pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients and bake in an 8 1/2 x 13-inch casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: esther's caramel cups
directions: Cut cream cheese and oleo into flour. Mix like for pie crust. Roll into balls.
Press into ungreased tassie pans.
Makes 48. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or light brown.

title: crichton's fudge
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and milk on medium heat, stirring frequently, until 236°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased plate. Cool and cut.

title: reduced-fat pie pastry
directions: Combine flour, Equal and salt in medium bowl; cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Mix in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with a fork after each additional until a dough is formed. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: fruit souffle
directions: In a
saucepan	dissolve
sugar in water and bring to a soft boil.
Add	syrup
mixture	to beaten egg whites slowly. Fold in fruit puree.
Put mixture in baking pan.
Place pan on a few small
rocks on bottom of Dutch oven.
Bake until light brown on top.
Serve with more puree.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 3
greased and floured 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: crullers
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then well beaten eggs.
Sift baking powder, nutmeg, salt and 1 cup flour.
Add, alternately with milk, to 1st mixture.
Add additional flour to make dough stiff enough to handle.
Toss on floured board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut into strips.
Twist and fry in deep fat (300° to 370°).
Drain on ungreased paper and when cool, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Scoop ice cream into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Serve immediately or place in freezer in shallow pan.
Cover.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Combine berries and lemon juice in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then remove from heat.
Add box of Sure-Jell and stir for 20 minutes.
Add Karo syrup and sugar and stir until well blended. Pour into a flat pan and let it set overnight, stirring occasionally.
Put into jars and freeze.
Makes 4 pints.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 13 1/2-inch baking dish; bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: pretzel crust strawberry salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix crushed pretzels and melted butter together. Put on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter; add peanut butter, cracker crumbs and sugar. Stir in nuts.
This makes a very stiff batter.
Form into balls the size of large walnuts.
Let them dry for four hours or overnight.
Melt the butterscotch bits with the paraffin and dip each cookie.
I keep the pan over hot water and use two forks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix Cheez Whiz and soup until well blended.
Chop cooked broccoli and add to cheese/soup mixture.
Stir well.
Mix in cooked rice and wheat germ.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Cut chicken breasts in strips.
Beat egg until foamy.
Soak chicken in egg mixture.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Brown strips in frying pan.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle mushrooms over top of chicken.
Put 2 teaspoons chicken broth to 1 1/2 cups water over chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kahlua kaper kake
directions: Oil 12 cup Bundt pan with Crisco and flour.
Blend all ingredients together until smooth, using electric mixer.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert onto serving platter. Dust with powdered sugar if desired.

title: small pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Place muffin halves under broiler and toast.
Add meat mixture and top with cheese.
May cut in 4 and use as hors d'oeuvres.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Stir biscuit mix and water together with a fork in a medium mixing bowl to form a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured surface.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough onto a square, 12 x 12-inch.
Cut square into 12 equal rectangles, each 4 x 3-inch. Wrap each rectangle into dough around 1 frankfurter.
Pinch edge of cardboard to fit into microwave.
Cover with wax paper.
Place franks on cardboard.
Brush with melted butter.
Cooking time is 7 minutes.
Recipe yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cup
directions: Blend all ingredients, except sugar.
Work in sugar until stiff.
It will be very stiff.
Mold into small circles and cover in chocolate.

title: corbin corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Add 1/2 of cheese with ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: uncooked chow chow
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together and put in jars.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Shred carrots.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate overnight.

title: chili
directions: In 5-quart or larger pan, put ground meat, chopped onion, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste and cumin.
Over medium heat, cook until meat is brown.
Take 1 or 1 1/2 cups grease off. Add red beans, tomato sauce, water, 5 tablespoons chili powder, salt and pepper to taste and 1 tablespoon cumin.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat down and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1 cup of the chopped pecans. Form ball and roll in remaining chopped pecans.
Roll in plastic wrap and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: south of the border chicken
directions: Combine the last 3 ingredients.
Soak corn tortillas in chicken broth and line baking pan with tortillas.
Place chicken top, then add onion, green pepper and cheese.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour soup mixture over top and sprinkle with chili powder.

title: escabesh(spanish cold fish dish)
directions: Wash and pat dry fish steaks.
In a large skillet pour vegetable oil and wait until hot.
Flour fish steaks and fry until done.
Remove fish from skillet and place in a large deep dish. Arrange fish so steaks don't sit on top of each other.
Set aside. In another skillet, pour olive oil.
Saute onions until clear, not fully cooked.
Add bay leaves, olives, garlic salt, pepper, salt and onion powder.
Stir.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over fish and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold. Serves 5.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into one or two balls. Roll in chopped pecans and dried parsley flakes.
Serve on crackers of choice.

title: meatloaf (barbecue style)
directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper, and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and put in shallow pan about 7x10 inches.
Combine the rest of sauce with all other ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake in moderate oven at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Baste occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place bottom pie crust in pie dish.
Mix in a bowl the vegetables, soup, onion and chicken broth to desired consistency. Pressure cook chicken.
Put vegetable mixture in pie crust.
Layer pieces of chicken on top.
Add small amount of additional broth if needed.
Put top crust on.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cookie bar
directions: Melt the butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cracker crumbs over butter.
Pat to make crust.
Add nuts, chips and coconut. Take the milk and pour over mixture, starting at edge.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl, making sure sugar is well dissolved.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: mocha buttercream frosting
directions: Melt butter/margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in the coffee and stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla.
Cream the remaining butter/margarine, sugar and cocoa. Gradually add the cooled pudding mixture, beating until frosting is fluffy and of spreading consistency.

title: favorite banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Mix dry ingredients (salt, soda and flour). Add to creamed butter. Add bananas and nuts. Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake in 250° to 300° oven for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Flatten chicken breasts between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Dip in flour and saute in oil and butter until tender.
Remove from pan.

title: wild rice baked in consomme
directions: Place rice in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add consomme; let stand 3 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes, adding a little water if rice becomes too dry.

title: bride's dessert
directions: Mix together lime Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold next 3 ingredients into Jell-O mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into Jell-O mixture.
Chill for several hours.

title: peanut butter and rice krispies treats
directions: Cook together the first 3 ingredients.
When all is blended well, add the cereal.
Pour in buttered dish.
Cut in squares.

title: creamy strawberry angel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour boiling water on gelatin in large bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate until thickened, but not set, about 1 hour. Slice strawberries, reserving a few berries for garnish if desired.
Fold in sliced strawberries and half of the whipped topping.
Refrigerate until thickened, but not set, about 15 minutes.
Split cake horizontally to make 3 layers.
(To split evenly, mark side of cake with wooden picks and cut with long thin knife.) Fill layers with gelatin mixture.
Spread remaining whipped topping over top.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles. Place on 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and sides to form crust.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat butter, sugar, potatoes, milk and eggs until well blended.
Pour into casserole dish or 10 x 15-inch cake pan.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar, corn flakes and nuts.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Excellent with turkey or ham dinner.

title: raisin soaked beets
directions: Drain beets, reserve 1/3 cup liquid.
In medium saucepan, combine reserved beet juice and raisins.
Cover.
Simmer until raisins are plumped, about 5 minutes.
Combine sugar and cornstarch, stir into raisins in pan.
Add lemon juice and butter, cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Stir in beets and simmer until mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes. Garnish with a twist of lemon.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix spices.
Rub on meat.
Wrap in foil and bake in pan for 8 hours at 225°.
Remove, unwrap and place in refrigerator.
When cold, slice.

title: easy caramel orange ring
directions: Grease Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Place orange marmalade by spoonfuls in pan and sprinkle nuts around the pan. Dip biscuits in melted margarine and then in the combined sugar and cinnamon.
Stand upright in Bundt pan creating a ring.
Pour extra margarine and sugar combination over completed ring.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn onto plate.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Skin, dice and cool.
Salt and pepper.
Boil eggs; chop.
Salt and pepper.
Chop celery, pickles, onion and pimiento.
Sprinkle with sugar and pickle juice.
Stir well.
Add salad dressing.
Add eggs to chopped mixture.
Fold potatoes into chopped mixture.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Let yeast and water set until dissolved.
Mix all ingredients. Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Roll out, cut and rise until doubled again.
Fry at 365°.
Add sugar or leave plain.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Line cooled pie shell with 2 cups blueberries.
Cook remaining berries with sugar, cornstarch, salt and water over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add butter and cool.
Pour over berries in shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Grease a pie pan.
Layer bottom of pan with vanilla wafers. Then cut up bananas in the cracks of the cookies.

title: coco-mac cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and set aside.
In large bowl, blend sugars.
Add butter and mix with beaters.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating at medium speed until fluffy.
Add coconut, flour mix and nuts.
Blend at low speed until just combined.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook onion and celery together with vinegar, sugar and mustard (add a little water).
Cook until tender.
Meanwhile, brown hamburger.
Salt to taste.
Add catsup and cooked vegetables to hamburger.
Simmer for flavor about 1/2 hour.

title: dieter's dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Cover and chill.
Will keep up to 5 days.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions and drain.
Mix with milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly onto cookie sheet.
Top with pizza sauce, pepperoni, cheese, mushrooms and additional toppings if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: incredible coconut pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add
eggs, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Pour into a deep dish 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken (or pork)
directions: Mix until smooth white vinegar, brown sugar, ground ginger, catsup and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and mix with corn and soup in casserole dish.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sweet-sour meat balls
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients.
Make meat balls small enough to handle on toothpicks.
Drop raw meat balls into mixer.
Simmer meat balls in mixture for 30 minutes.

title: 5 alarm chili
directions: Brown all meat with onions, chili peppers and chili mix; pour off grease.
Pour in tomatoes and tomato juice; simmer for 3 1/2 hours.
Add beans and Ro-Tel; simmer for additional hour.
Serves 25 to 30 bowls.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup and pudding mix in a bowl.
Add milk and egg. Stir to blend.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: fruit slush dessert(no fat)
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add orange juice, bananas and pineapple, stirring until orange juice is dissolved.
Stir in 7-Up, then pour into large container or several small containers. Freeze.
Thaw approximately 1 hour or until slushy before serving. Can add fresh, sliced peaches or seedless grapes before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix soups and broth together.
Set aside.
Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Drain Veg-All and pour over chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and vegetables.

title: meat loaf with tomato sauce
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the sauce and use 1 cup of sauce with the meat mixture. Shape into a loaf in greased dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix the cheese, chives and cubed chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread out crescent roll triangle and stretch somewhat.
Fill each triangle with chicken mixture and wrap dough around it and seal.
Roll bundles in butter, then in stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: nut fudge
directions: Place sugar and evaporated milk in large medium-to-heavy saucepan.
Cut 6 tablespoons of butter and the marshmallows (small pieces, 5 or 6 to each) into mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until marshmallows have melted and mixture bubbles all over top.
Cook and stir for 5 to 6 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and immediately add chocolate bits and remaining butter.
Stir until chocolate pieces have dissolved.
Stir in walnuts (or whichever kind you prefer).
Pour into shallow baking pan (at least 8 x 8-inches) and allow to cool before cutting.

title: snow cream
directions: Be sure to use clean snow.
The best is usually scraped off a car hood.
All mixed together provides a really tasty treat.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Melt butter and blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir in chicken broth and cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sauce thickens.
Stir in wine.
Arrange broccoli and chicken in greased casserole dish.
Pour in sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: paella ala valenciana
directions: Heat oil in a paella pan.
If not available, use a 12 to 14-inch skillet.
Add chicken and saute until brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: double fudge mint brownies
directions: Melt; spread on top.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Drain blueberries, reserving 2/3 cup juice.
Add blueberries and juice and pineapple with its juice to jello. Chill until set.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy.
Add pecans and other ingredients.
Make sure nuts are covered completely.
Put on buttered pan and bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Take out every 15 minutes and stir.

title: french fry casserole
directions: Place hamburger in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put onions over hamburger.
Mix soups together and pour over onions.
Place French fries on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
This recipe can be cut in half by using 8 x 8-inch pan and freezing half of the soup mixture.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.
Yields 6 cups.

title: tomato-onion-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart casserole. In 1 inch of boiling water in a medium saucepan, cook onion, covered, 10 minutes; drain.

title: grandma's skillet cookies
directions: In heavy skillet, at low temperature, cook beaten egg, sugar, butter and dates until dates pull away from the side of skillet. Add nuts, gumdrops and vanilla.
Pour over cereal; stir and cool. Roll in 1-inch balls in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: seafood delight
directions: Thaw fish, cut into 1-inch chunks.
Heat oil, butter, onions and garlic in heavy skillet.
Saute about 2 minutes or until onion is soft.
Add tomatoes, wine, water, parsley, basil, salt and oregano.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine
vinegar,
vegetable oil, salt, sugar, water and pepper.
Bring
to
a
boil, stirring to dissolve sugar;
cool. Drain
vegetables
and place in Tupperware container or jar and stir
in
vinegar mixture.
Cover, place in refrigerator for 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cauliflower, broccoli, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
In smaller bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Mix well and spoon over vegetables and toss well until they are all coated.
Chill and toss again when serving.

title: mexican bean dip(fat free)
directions: Mix together and serve over Guiltless Gourmet tortilla chips.

title: vanilla drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: pralines
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until soft ball stage (you can roll between your fingers), on medium heat.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Beat until thick.
Drop (fast) on wax paper with spoon.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Alternate layers of vegetables. Combine remaining ingredients; heat.
Beat to blend, then cool while carrots are cooking.
Pour dressing over vegetables; let stand at least a day.
Put on lettuce leaves with a slotted spoon to serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add rice and sauces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar and milk; stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken with cheese
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan. Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Mix 1/4 cup water and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over cheese.
Pour on 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine.
Put croutons on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: easy pork chop bake
directions: In a large saucepan, heat mushroom and chicken soups, water and rice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chops on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle dry onion soup evenly over chops. Sprinkle with paprika.
Dot each chop with butter.
Cover with foil and bake in the oven at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until brown.
Extra 30 minutes may not be needed.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season chops with salt.
Place in a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan or large baking dish.
Top each chop with an onion slice and with a lemon slice.
Place one tablespoon brown sugar and one tablespoon ketchup on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour; uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all together, except cheese, and pour into a large, ovenproof bowl.
Cover with Jack and/or Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from whole corn into measuring cup, noting the amount.
Discard the liquid.
Pour milk into same measuring cup until amount equals liquid that was discarded.
Put corn into medium-sized casserole dish.
Add butter, milk and cheese to the corn.
Add green pepper and onion, if desired.
Mix well.
Crumble crackers into mixture.
Stir.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Dish is done when top starts to brown and mixture appears set.
Remove from oven and let cool for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water over oatmeal; let stand 20 minutes.
Combine margarine and sugars.
Add beaten eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well, then add oatmeal mixture.
Add flour and soda.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: klaver vier koekjes(cookies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cocoa and vanilla.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Mix vanilla with 1/2 of dough, cocoa with the other half of dough.
Shape in 4 rolls, 2 white, 2 chocolate. Arrange chocolate and vanilla rolls checkerboard fashion and wrap as one roll in waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator for half hour. Cut in slices.
Bake on greased baking sheets (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy 6 week pickles
directions: Pack
large-mouth jars or
jugs
(I
use
gallon)
with washed cucumbers.	Pour apple cider vinegar to cover.
Crumple tinfoil to go on top if cukes	float.	Put
on
lid,
place in grocery bag and put in cabinet or closet for 6 weeks.
Remove; pour off vinegar and rinse
cucumbers.
Trim,
weigh
and
use same weight of sugar.
Slice (any
way	you
like)
into
jug, layering cucumbers and sugar until
finished.
Put
on lid and put back in closet until sugar is dissolved.
After dissolved, put small amount in jar in refrigerator to crisp and eat.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat egg.
Beat in oil, milk and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in muffin pan for 25 minutes. Remove immediately.
Freeze, if desired, for later use.

title: creamy potato cheese soup(the secret is the cream cheese.)
directions: Cover veggies with water. Boil until tender. Drain. Mix margarine, soup, cream cheese in mixing bowl. Stir well. Add milk, salt, pepper, and bacon. Add to veggies. Heat through. Serve.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine melted butter with sugar, cocoa and egg yolks.
Stir well; add milk gradually.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until custard is firm. Top with meringue.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in peanut butter with a fork.
Add egg and milk; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 450° until cheese melts.
Serve on party rye bread slices.

title: honey sweet and sour sauce(for pork, rice or noodles)
directions: Combine honey, vinegar, jelly, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce and dry mustard in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Combine cornstarch in 1/4 cup water and stir into hot mixture. Add pineapple, green pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour over pork, chicken fillets or rice or noodles.

title: dorito chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and skin.
Add soups and broth from chicken (approximately 1 can) and Ro-Tel and mix together.
Place chips, then chicken and soup mixture.
Cook in oven until cheeses are melted.

title: golden tea punch
directions: Stir instant tea into water until dissolved.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add juices.
Chill.
Pour punch into bowl and add ginger ale.
Add an ice mold to punch to chill.
Serves 18.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup milk over low heat.
Add remaining milk.
Remove from heat.
Chill until set.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in baking dish.
Pour preserves over.
Mix dressing, onion soup and water.
Stir and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered with foil.
Take foil off and add pineapple and pepper strips; bake 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add water, vanilla and oil.
Mix well and spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about an hour.
Stir frequently.
Should be light brown when done.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Roll biscuit quarters in flour and place in 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Melt butter, sugar and milk and pour over biscuits. Sprinkle with cinnamon and place in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Mix some of your flour with the mixed fruit and nuts to keep them from sticking together.
Combine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: swedish toast(cookie bars)
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg and yolk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add flavoring last.
Spread on a 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Brush over dough.
Sprinkle on almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Take out of oven and cut into squares.
Turn off oven and put cookie sheet back in oven; leave overnight.*
Store in tightly sealed container.

title: lollipops
directions: You will also need 18 lollipop sticks.
Lightly butter 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet.
Arrange lollipop sticks on baking sheet. Combine butter, syrup and sugar in 1-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cook until hard boil stage (270°).
Stir in food coloring and vanilla. Drop by teaspoons over end of each lollipop stick.

title: brown sugar banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas.

title: bean and bacon casserole
directions: In large skillet, combine onion, garlic powder, dry mustard, brown sugar and vinegar.
Cover and cook over heat.
Combine beans in an ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Stir in bacon and onion mixture.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: chocolate eclairs made easy
directions: Beat pudding and milk 2 minutes then fold in Cool Whip; set aside.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix egg, sugar, lemon juice and milk in small saucepan.
Add vinegar after the addition of milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Pour over fruit and 1/2 package of marshmallows placed in a 4-quart dish.
If you want more marshmallows, add to mixture and mix.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans well and mix with mushroom soup and onion. Bake at 350° until center boils, approximately 40 minutes.

title: char's corned beef-onion sandwich spread
directions: Mix all together and spread on white or dark bread.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add
alternately
with
water and vanilla.
Stir in apricots and nuts.	Bake in well-greased small bread cans or 4 well-greased No. 2 round cans.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pineapple casserole(great served with ham)
directions: Drain
both cans of pineapple, keeping 8 tablespoons of juice. Add
sugar	and
flour
to 8 tablespoons of juice.	Mix together. Combine with pineapple and add Cheddar cheese.
Mix all together and
put
in baking casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30
minutes. At this time, have butter melted and crackers crushed.
Mix crackers
and butter together and add to top of casserole.	Bake an additional 30 minutes for total of 1 hour baking time. Can also be made in advance and refrigerated.

title: soy sauce rice
directions: Cook first 6 items together slowly for 5 minutes.
Place cooled rice in casserole.
Pour sauce over rice and mix together. Add almonds, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cube steaks in onion soup
directions: Dredge cube steaks in flour that has been seasoned.
Brown in oil and pour off all excess oil.
Add onion soup and wine.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: chocolate eclair and frosting
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Put layer of crackers; mix until used.
Always have crackers on bottom and top. Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Soften butter and add.
Stir until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Add next 3 ingredients and optional items.
Mix until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased pan (use Pam in the loaf pan).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to rack to cool completely.
Makes one 9-inch loaf.

title: black-eyed peas skillet dinner
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper until beef is brown; drain fat.
Add peas, tomatoes, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Save 1/2 cup pecans to roll ball in.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Butter and flour Bundt pan.
Cream melted butter with sugar. Add remaining ingredients in order named.
Place 1/3 of batter in a 9-inch tube pan.
Cover with half of mixture you have prepared of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Place another layer of batter in pan and cover with remaining mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place the rest of the batter in pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and invert pan.

title: mammaw's ripe tomato catsup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan.
Boil for 2 hours on top of stove, stirring constantly, especially the last 45 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Put all ingredients into a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered for 25 minutes, stirring often.
Let cool until you can touch.
Push through a strainer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mile high lemonade pie
directions: Chill milk in an ice tray until almost frozen.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and frozen lemonade.
Stir until lemonade thaws. Chill until mixture is thick.
Whip iced milk until stiff; fold into gelatin. Put in coconut or graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 hours in refrigerator.
This makes a nice big pie (9 inch pan).

title: fast and easy dessert
directions: In a large casserole dish, make a layer of cookies that have been
dipped in sweet milk (don't leave cookies in milk; dip and take out).	Cover cookies with Cool Whip.
Make 2 more layers of cookies covered with Cool Whip.
Dip with a spoon to serve. Delicious and good when you need something fast.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Parboil chicken in boiling water 5 minutes.
In saucepot, saute onions, celery and carrots in margarine 5 minutes.
Blend in flour to absorb all liquid.
Add chicken stock, bouillon cube, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Boil slowly, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes.
Turn down heat.
Add chicken and rice. Adjust seasoning.

title: dressing balls
directions: Melt oleo in frypan; add celery and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add to dressing mix along with egg and broth.
Form into balls and place in a baking dish or pan.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil, margarine and vanilla in a large bowl with mixer until fluffy.
Add egg and beat.
Sift dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten a little.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: nora's pizza
directions: Place dough on greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Spread olive oil to top of uncooked dough.
Place sliced tomato (shape of half moon) on top of oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 425° for approximately 8 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown.

title: rum balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Roll into balls; cover with powdered sugar.

title: peas and peanut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish and add rice and zucchini.
Mix together mushroom soup, water, salt, pepper, onions, mushrooms and cheese.
Pour over casserole.
Make sure all rice is moistened. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: spicy nuts
directions: Combine sugar, salt, spices and water in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved. Continue to cook, without stirring, until the mixture registers 238° on a candy thermometer or forms a soft ball.
Add nuts and turn onto wax paper.

title: nanny's jello
directions: Add boiling water to the jello and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until partially set, approximately 2 hours.
Add yogurt.
Whip with mixer.
Return to fridge until set.

title: ginger peachy chicken
directions: Cook chicken in margarine in skillet.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Drain syrup from peaches, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Stir in the cornstarch and ground ginger. Add mixture to skillet and stir into chicken drippings.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add peaches and heat through.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chicken strips over cooked rice and spoon mixture over chicken.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in hot water, then add cold water. Add pineapple and orange juice.
Next, mix lemonade according to directions on can, then add to mixture.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: marion's lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour until well blended, then add lemon juice.
Pour over the baked crust; bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from the oven and allow to cool before cutting to serve.

title: california presbyterian chicken
directions: Marinate
bite-size chicken pieces in olive oil, garlic and herbs
for	a
few	hours.	Saute onion in olive oil; add chicken (and
its
marinade)
and
saute until done.
Toss in large serving
bowl
with 3/4 pound of hot fettuccine and all the remaining ingredients.
The Feta cheese will melt a bit.

title: gail's beef brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover brisket.
Cover with foil.
Cook for 1 hour per pound at 300°, approximately 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: curried pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown lightly on both sides of frying pan.
Place in baking pan.
Cover with mushrooms (drained).
Cook finely chopped onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and curry powder.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over chops.
Cover pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: new year's dinner
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a little vegetable oil. Add onion and about 1 cup water. Cover; cook 45 minutes. Add sauerkraut and sugar. Cook 1/2 hour longer until meat is very tender. Boil small whole red-skinned potatoes and cook black-eyed peas for an All American New Year's dinner. Said to bring good luck for the whole year.

title: cherry berry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries until almost melted.
Add can of pineapple and cranberry sauce. Add nuts and marshmallows if desired.
Pour in mold or desired dish and refrigerate.

title: chicken with ritz crackers
directions: Soak
chicken
in
milk.
Crush
Ritz crackers and toss with salt, pepper, cheese and parsley.
Roll chicken pieces in cracker mixture.
Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top
with
a
piece
of butter.
Add just enough hot water to cover
the	bottom of the baking dish.
Bake at 350° for
1/2 hour, uncovered.
Cover with foil and continue baking for 1/2 hour.

title: pot pie
directions: Combine flour, lard, salt and eggs.
Mix as you would for a pie crust.
Add enough water to roll out on a floured surface. Roll out to 1/8-inch or up to 1/4-inch thick and cut in 1-inch squares.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes in either beef or chicken broth that has been brought to a boil.
This recipe is over 100 years old.

title: apple-spice bread(for bread-maker)
directions: Mix the apple pie spice with the flour.
Measure all ingredients into your bread machine in the order your machine suggests.
Add dried apples on the "Mix Bread" cycle, if you have it, otherwise as manufacturer suggests.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into loaf.
Place in a pan.
Use tomato juice to pour around loaf to keep bottom of pan from burning.
Bake for about 45 minutes or an hour.
When done, take out, slice and serve.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add the soup.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes. Stir in the sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve over noodles.
Also can be served over toast, potatoes or elbow or ziti.

title: betty's quick casserole
directions: Fry hamburg and onions lightly; drain.	Place on bottom of casserole.	Top
with
frozen
Tater Tots.	Add chicken and celery soup; spread
over Tater Tots.
Do not add water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until light brown on top.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add gravy and simmer.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat oil, brown celery, onions and mushrooms.
Mix all together and cook over kerosene fuel for 4 weeks at 465°.
Yields 3,800 or more servings.

title: upside-down dinner casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with bacon slices.
Press the ground beef on top of bacon.
Follow with sliced onions and carrots.
Sift the flour over the carrots and add sliced potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour the soup over the top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: holiday mashed potato onion puff
directions: Peel, cook and mash the potatoes in ricer.
Work fast and keep warm.
Melt butter and cream in microwave if possible.
Add the egg yolks to mashed potatoes and fold in melted butter and cream. (Note:
If more milk or cream is needed, add.)
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Add a pinch of cream of tartar.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Mix in order given. Roll 1/2-inch thick and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown at 375°.
Frost with powdered sugar.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks.
Mash the egg yolks and blend in mayo or salad dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refill egg halves.

title: seasoned snack
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Pour over crackers and mix together well.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 325° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and stir well.
Return to oven for 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Soak yeast in 2 cups of lukewarm water for 1/2 hour.
Stir in flour.
Cover and let set overnight.
Next morning, use remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook as you would for regular pancakes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Partly peel the cucumber, leaving a little green peel on here and there for color.
Slice thin.
Slice the onion and separate the rings.
Stir together the vinegar, water, sugar and oregano. Stir together.
Do a couple of hours before the meal.
Serve at room temperature and refrigerate after the meal.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Mix together meat, 1/4 cup onions, celery, 1/2 cup chopped mushrooms, 2/3 of the garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook; drain fat. Add butter, 1/2 pound mushrooms, remaining onion and garlic and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Reduce heat and simmer until sauce is heated, about 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, Cap'n Crunch, pretzels and peanuts in large bowl.
Melt almond bark in microwave according to package directions.
Pour bark over ingredients in bowl and mix with wooden spoon.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let dry and store in airtight container.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans.
Soak beans overnight.
Saute garlic and onion.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Add cooked beans and pineapple. Stir and place in casserole.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch round pans; line bottom with wax paper.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mild chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions in skillet; discard grease. Mix all ingredients in large cooking pot and simmer for 2 hours or until thoroughly cooked and blended. Serves 10.

title: lemon pie
directions: Spread Parkay into bottom of a casserole dish. Place whole wafers in bottom of dish, filling in spaces with crushed wafers. In a bowl, mix lemon juice and milk. Add half of the Cool Whip. Pour into the casserole dish. Top with remainder of Cool Whip. Keep in the refrigerator. This freezes well.

title: oatmeal tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, oats, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs, applesauce, raisins, oil and milk in a bowl.
Make a well in reserved flour mixture.
Stir in applesauce mixture by hand into flour until flour is just moistened.
Grease 1 loaf pan.
Turn batter into pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, cheese, onion and sour cream.
Pour over beans and corn. Mix melted margarine with crackers and almonds.
Sprinkle crushed mixture over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, substituting chicken broth for the water.
Mix cooked rice with sour cream. Preheat oven to 350°.
Put half of rice mixture in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Layer half the chilies and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sesame seed sticks
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
With blender, cut in shortening until mixture has look of large crumbs.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix with fork just until dough holds together.
Knead several times until smooth.
Shape tablespoon of dough into ovals. Roll in seed.
Bake at 375° (190°C) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together the cornstarch, sugar, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in beet juice and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in beets; heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: beans and franks
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine onion with remaining ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: nut twists
directions: Mix baking mix, milk, 2 tablespoons granulated sugar and the egg until dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Turn onto surface well dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Knead 10 times.
Roll dough into 12-inch squares; spread with margarine.
Mix walnuts and brown sugar; sprinkle evenly over margarine.
Fold dough into thirds; press edges together to seal securely.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch strips.
Twist ends of strips in opposite direction.

title: poulet a la moutarde(mustard chicken)
directions: Brush chickens with combined butter and oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place 5 inches from the broiler and broil chicken 20 minutes on each side.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of butter from broiling pan into a saucepan and saute scallions 4 minutes until tender. Stir in mustard and flour.
Add chicken broth, tomato paste, lemon juice and thyme.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve hot.

title: finikia
directions: Soak farina, juice and soda until thick.
Cream Crisco and oil, about 10 minutes.
Add sugar, some flour and farina mixture. Mix well.
Add the rest of the flour (sifted) to make a medium dough that does not stick to hands.

title: lasagna wannabe
directions: Cook noodles in 3-quarts of boiling salt water.
(One teaspoon of oil in water will help keep noodles from sticking together).
Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon butter and drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream; add onions and green pepper.
Spread half of cooked noodles in a greased casserole; cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles. Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over noodles.
Put meat sauce on top.
Bake at 360° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and paprika.
Drain vegetables.
Pour mixture over.
Set 24 hours in refrigerator. Drain before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook as much macaroni as you want for casserole.
Drain and blanch with cool water.
Butter casserole dish.
Cover bottom with macaroni.
Lay cheese slices side by side to cover macaroni.
Add 4 to 5 dabs butter, then another layer macaroni, cheese and butter until macaroni is used.
Sprinkle with pepper and fill bowl about 1/2 full of milk.
Bake in 350° oven until milk has cooked through and browned on top.

title: honey chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift baking powder, flour and salt.
Cream the shortening and honey.
Beat in egg.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Process peaches in the blender. Add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil sliced carrots until tender; drain.
Mix dry ingredients. Add tomato soup, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over carrots, onion and bell pepper.
Marinate overnight.

title: baked carrots and sweet basil
directions: Scrape, peel and slice carrots and place in a baking dish. In a pan mix hot water, salt, margarine, minced onion and sweet basil.
Mix together and pour over carrots.
Bake, covered, at 375° until carrots are done.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Lay crackers on bottom of pan.
Cover with prepared pudding. Top with chosen fruit, then whipped topping.
Makes 4 servings (1 B., 1 F., 1/2 milk and 20 optional).

title: pasta salad
directions: Stir dressing and noodles.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.
Serve chilled or warm.

title: layered ham and chicken casserole
directions: Combine meats, vegetables, eggs, pimento and olives.
Mix 2 cans of soup.
Place a layer of noodles in a well-buttered casserole dish (2 1/2 to 3-quart size).
Add a layer of meat mixture and a layer of soup.
Alternate layers until all ingredients have been used, ending with soup.
Top with crushed potato chips or seasoned bread crumbs.

title: corn bread mix
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, milk powder and salt in large bowl. Cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store in covered airtight container in cool place up to 6 weeks.
Stir mix lightly into measuring cup and level off with a knife.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill in freezer.
Beat pudding mix and milk together.
Mix with softened ice cream and spread over cracker crust.
Chill in freezer until firm.
Spread whipped topping over dessert and garnish as desired.

title: chicken mess
directions: Saute onion in a little butter.
Add all liquids and some water. Cook together for a few minutes. Add chicken and chips. Simmer for a few minutes longer.
Add peppers, if you like it hot. Cover with grated cheese and brown just until cheese melts.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Put fresh berries in pie shell, reserving 1 cup of berries. Put the one cup of berries, sugar, water and cornstarch (dissolved in a small amount of water) into a saucepan.
Cook until it boils and is thick.
Pour cooked mixture (slightly cooled) over berries in the pie shell.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: jean's salad dressing
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until thick, then add pepper and celery.

title: fruited pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides; place in casserole.
Top with apple, onion and seasonings.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and top with pineapple slice.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes or until pineapple is tipped with brown.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir just enough to mix pieces.
Cover and set on low for 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in pan.
Stir in 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling;
stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle dry milk and water; stir until smooth.
Add vanilla if wanted.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage.
Place in salted, boiling water to cover.
Cut off leaves as they become wilted.
Drain.
Trim thick center vein of each leaf.
Brown onion in Crisco.
Add meat, seasonings and rice and mix well.
Place tablespoon of filling on each cabbage leaf and roll.
Place in pot and cover 2/3 full with water.
Add sauerkraut and tomato juice on top.
Cover and cook slowly 1 1/2 hours until rice is done.
Pour sour cream on top and cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: swiss cheese cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 12 x 7 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: overnight chicken salad
directions: *Mix a 0.4-ounce package of buttermilk dressing mix according to directions.
Use 1/3 cup for this recipe and refrigerate the rest.
Stays fresh 3 to 4 weeks.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and lemon juice.
Mix well. Add raisins and water. Stir over low heat until it thickens. Remove from heat and add butter.
Makes about 2 cups.
Is delicious served on baked ham.

title: quick bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 1-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High for
minutes.
Stir,
then microwave approximately 1 more minute.
Serve with chips or by itself.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, water, egg yolks and lemon juice. (Set egg whites aside to be used for meringue.) Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.

title: mock german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 3 lightly greased 9-inch round cake pans with wax paper.
Melt carob chips in water and stir.
Make certain all chips are completely melted; set aside. Mix flour, baking powder and salt (optional); set aside.
Beat margarine and dry sweetener in large mixing bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks (egg replacer mixture).
Stir in carob mixture with vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with soy milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites (egg replacer mixture) in another bowl with electric mixer on high speed until fluffy.
Gently stir into batter.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool and remove from pans.
Peel wax paper off bottom.
Cool completely on wire racks before frosting.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and well beaten eggs.
Beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients with sour cream.
Mix cocoa and hot water and add to the batter.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread with chocolate icing.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef. Cook rice. Mix everything together and simmer until peppers and onions are tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Will keep refrigerated for several days.
Should be a good pink color.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Reserve juice.
Chop pineapple, peaches and pears in large pieces.
Slice bananas; place in large bowl.
Mix pudding with reserved juice.
Mix well and pour over fruit.
Chill before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture along with sour cream.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Don't use Bundt pan!

title: macaroni and cheese meal
directions: In a covered 2 1/2 to 3-quart pan, microwave macaroni in 3 cups water for 5 minutes.
Drain and add cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into the deep dish pie crust, topping with regular pie crust.
Place in 450° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes or until top crust is golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Blend oil, vinegar and spices.
Add to other ingredients. Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: crab and rice primavera
directions: Bring vegetables and water to boil in medium saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes. Add milk, imitation crabmeat, margarine, garlic powder and basil. Bring to full boil.
Stir in rice and cheese.
Cover, remove from heat, and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: You will need 12 muffin cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; let cool.
Pick chicken off the bone. Moisten 1/2 of stuffing with 1/2 of margarine and place in bottom of large baking dish.
Place pieces of chicken on the stuffing; add soups and broth.
Top with remaining stuffing moistened with remaining margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes a large casserole.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Wrap each chestnut with 1/2 strip of bacon.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add sugar and ketchup mix. Pour over top and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: good vegetable chili
directions: Soak beans overnight per directions on bag.
The water used to soak the kidney beans can be used later, but the water from the black beans cannot.
Cut green and red peppers into strips, about 1/4-inch wide by 1-inch long.
Chop the hot peppers and garlic separately.
Cut the tomatoes in half and then in thin slices. Saute peppers in olive oil on low heat.
When peppers are soft, add garlic and if necessary, more olive oil to keep moist.
Allow garlic to cook a few minutes and then add tomatoes.
When tomatoes are cooked for about 10 minutes, add cumin, rice and salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Heat soup, milk and cheese together. Stir until cheese is melted.
Combine macaroni, cheese sauce, vegetables, tuna, 1 cup onion and seasoning.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated well.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and then add the dressing. Refrigerate.

title: jello salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cream cheese and marshmallows in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Add boiling water; mix well and let stand a few minutes to cool.
Add pineapple.
Mix in almost all of a small container of Cool Whip.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill to set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat together the butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat again.
Add 1/4 cup flour and beat again.
Chill in refrigerator.
Form small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy opera fudge(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass bowl, micro-melt the butter about 1 minute. Stir in dry mix and milk.
Micro-cook, uncovered, until boiling, about 3 minutes; stir occasionally.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring every 15 seconds.
Add vanilla.
Beat in sugar; stir in nuts or cherries.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients. Roll in additional chopped nuts. Makes 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Blend buttermilk into pudding mix (dry), using medium speed. When smooth, blend in Cool Whip.
If consistency of mixture seems too thick, add a little more buttermilk.

title: beef-o-roni
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in the oil and drain.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Mix tomato soup and milk together.
Combine all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tortellini alfredo
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package, adding broccoli the last 3 minutes of pasta cooking time. Drain. Heat sauce and chicken in saucepan. Toss in all ingredients. Serves 3.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Add crawfish tails; cook, covered, over low heat about 20 minutes.
Add green onions and small amount of water for desired consistency.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Let the margarine and cream cheese sit at room temperature for a while.
Mix together and add the powdered sugar and almond extract.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice.
When hot, stir in cornstarch, 2 eggs, sugar and salt already mixed together.
Take off heat and cool. In bowl, mix pineapple, fruit cocktail, marshmallows and walnuts. When liquid is cool, add all ingredients.
Add in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: a side dish of mushrooms
directions: Serve mushrooms often as a major vegetable.
Here is a very quick way to prepare an impressive dish of mushrooms.

title: sausage cheese biscuits
directions: Gently fry the sausage, breaking it up as you fry it.
Mix the shredded cheese and Bisquick in a large mixing bowl.
Add sausage, drippings and all.
Blend well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 50.

title: mom's chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook chicken in water.
Cool broth; skim off fat.
Skin and bone chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Add to broth with remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Make 2 vanilla wafer crusts.
Mix ingredients and pour into crusts.
Freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Lightly spray an unheated large saucepan with non stick spray. Add onion and celery, cook over medium heat until onions are tender.
Stir in broth and rice.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: The sauce can be prepared in the time it takes to bring the water to a boil.
In a small saucepan; add olive oil, garlic and salt.
Saute this over low heat until it becomes golden, rich brown, stirring often.
Place spaghetti into boiling water; cook until tender yet firm to bite.
For regular to thick paste, boil about 7 minutes.
This is how the Italians like it best!
Drain the pasta immediately and place into a warm bowl.
There is no need to rinse it if it is cooked al dente.
Add the hot garlic, oil and salt to pasta and toss rapidly, coating all strands and add pepper and parsley.
Mix the remaining teaspoon of oil with the pasta and serve immediately.
This is a good appetizer to hearty meal or with a salad as a low-fat, low cholesterol meal.
Be sure to sprinkle the pasta with freshly grated Romano or Parmesan cheese.

title: continental sandwiches
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; add mayonnaise and season to taste. Serve on toasted bread with a slice of tomato and lettuce. Makes a delicious sandwich.

title: parmesan crisps
directions: Cut wonton skins in half diagonally.
Arrange wonton skins in a single layer on baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray. Combine water and next 5 ingredients.
Brush evenly on triangles and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Store in airtight container.
Yields about 40 crisps, 15 calories per crisp, 0.4 gm fat, 1 mg cholesterol.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in tightly fitting jar.

title: no-crust apple pie
directions: Mix apple slices with sugar, cinnamon and water in saucepan. Cook 10 minutes or until apples are partially cooked.
Turn into baking dish.

title: hot mexican chili
directions: Fry meat until brown with a little oil.
Move meat to side of pan.
With the oil, take 2 Tbsp. flour and make a paste.
Stir with meat and add remaining ingredients.

title: shanila's lentil soup(mung ki dal)
directions: Wash mung dal until water washes clean.
Put dal in pot.
Add water, turmeric, red pepper and salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover pan partially and simmer for 30 minutes, or until dal is tender, but still intact.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon in 12-inch skillet until crisp.
Add vinegar; heat through. Remove from heat; add lettuce and onions.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper; toss until lettuce is wilted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: curried fruit
directions: Make up ahead of time.
Drain fruit well.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole in layers using cherries on top.
Melt butter; add sugar and curry, then spoon over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Makes 12 servings.

title: blueberry turnovers
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup of the sugar, salt, egg yolks, flour and milk together until well blended and a soft dough is formed, then chill for 1 hour.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness and cut out 5 to 6 inch rounds.
Mix the blueberries with the brown sugar, tapioca and orange rind and spoon on the rounds.
Moisten edges of each round with water.
Fold dough over filling and press together.
Prick top with a fork and place turnovers on a greased cookie sheet.
Beat the egg whites until foamy, then beat in 1/3 cup sugar gradually.
Brush mixture on top of turnovers.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until turnovers are lightly browned.
Yields 12 turnovers.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 16.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Use 1/2 can pumpkin and 1/2 can squash.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (sprayed) and 1/2 full another loaf pan.
Make another batch. Fill 2 more loaf pans and fill leftover 1/2 loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until dry.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: bean pot stew
directions: Combine all in casserole with lid (bean pot). Bake 5 hours at 250°.
Add package of frozen peas during the last hour.

title: paw's favorite chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: tasty green salad
directions: Put in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish in the order given.
Cover tightly and chill at least 10 hours.
It is very pretty in a clear glass bowl.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Cut pineapple chunks in half, if you wish.
If you are using sugar, combine it with cream cheese and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add all other ingredients and stir to coat fruit.
Place in freezer for at least 1 hour before serving.
If kept in freezer, as a reserve for unexpected guests, remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: doo - dads(crunchy munchies)
directions: Mix margarine, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce in little dish and melt in microwave 1 minute.
Mix all "crunchies" together and toss with liquid mix.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Stir.
Microwave 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave 1 final minute. Spread on paper towel covered cookie sheet to cool.
When cooled and crispy, jar up or put up in Ziploc baggies.

title: raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Beat egg yolks slightly in top of double boiler.
Add syrup and cook over hot water until mixture thickens slightly.
Remove from stove and add softened gelatin. Stir until dissolved; cool.
Combine raspberries and lemon juice and add to other mixture.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff, but not dry, gradually beating in sugar.
Fold into raspberry mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pile into pastry shell.
Chill thoroughly before serving. May be garnished with whipped cream and berries.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, cheese and rice together. Put in 9 x 13 dish. Put chicken on top of rice. Open another can of cream of chicken or cream of mushroom; pour over the chicken. Spread with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and milk in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay pieces of the cut-up chicken on top of rice mixture.
Cover with dry onion soup, salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: anise cutout cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and 1 cup sugar until fluffy; add eggs and aniseed.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to the creamed mixture.
Add apple juice and mix well. On a floured surface, knead until well blended, about 4-5 minutes. Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness; cut into 2 inch shapes.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12-16 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon, roll cookies in the mixture while still warm. cool on wire racks.
Yield:
About 5 dozen.

title: veal cutlet supreme
directions: Season veal with salt and garlic powder.
Dip in egg; then dip in bread crumbs.
Fry in butter until browned on both sides. Remove and place in baking pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Saute onions until tender (soft) slowly, seasoning with salt and paprika.
Add water during latter stages of cooking and simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Place slice of cheese on top of veal pieces, then pour onion gravy on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix ground beef with salt, pepper, egg, minced onion and bread crumbs.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Brown in hot oil. Remove meatballs from skillet.
Pour off all fat, except 3 tablespoons.
Blend in flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer over low heat 10 minutes, adding more water if necessary.
Pour over meatballs in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in a moderate 350° oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
This may also be cooked on top of stove if simmered slowly.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to countertop.

title: miss rose's home fries
directions: Place Potatoes in microwave and cook on high for approximately 10 minutes. Check the tenderness of the potatoes. If more time is needed, cook a few minutes at a time so as not to overcook them.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder;
add to creamed mixture.
Add rolled oats and stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: You will need paper muffin cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in a mixing bowl; mix together.
Add carrots, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350 for one hour.
Stir at 15 minute intervals.
Serve as a hot dessert a la mode.

title: raspberry and pudding treat
directions: Use four 8-ounce dessert dishes.
Divide raspberries in dessert dishes; set aside.
Combine boiling water and gelatin in bowl until dissolved.
Add ice cubes to cold water to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove unmelted ice.
Pour gelatin in each dessert dish.
Refrigerate 20 minutes until partially set.

title: zucchini saute
directions: Wash zucchini but do not peel.
Slice in rounds about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix remaining ingredients except oil.
Toss zucchini in mixture until well distributed.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add zucchini and saute until browned on both sides, about 10 minutes. Drain on paper towel.
Goes well with any meat.
Serves 4.

title: quick and jazzy jambalaya
directions: In just 30 minutes, you can now make a delicious main dish with a box of Rice-A-Roni and a few simple ingredients.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Lightly spray 13 x 9-inch glass pan with Pam.
Layer hash browns in bottom of pan.
Combine mushroom soup, chicken soup, sour cream and 1 cup cheese.
Pour over hash browns.
Top with 1 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese on top is bubbly brown.

title: spam stroganoff
directions: Cut Spam into cubes.
Brown Spam, onions and mushrooms in a large skillet.
Mix mushroom soup and milk together.
Add soup mixture to Spam in skillet.
Let simmer about 15 minutes; stir frequently.

title: reece's peanut butter cups
directions: Slice cookie dough and roll into ball.
Put ball in small greased muffin pan.
Make thumb print indent into ball.
Bake at 350 for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put peanut butter cup into center of cookie.
Remove immediately from muffin pan to cool. Makes 36 cookies.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions; drain well.
Mix eggs, soup and milk. Layer sausage, Rice Krispies, then cheese.
Cover with egg mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix with hot water; serve.

title: citrus slice cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend in flour and salt.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
To one part, work in a few drops yellow food color and the lemon peel. Repeat with green food coloring and lime peel, yellow/red food coloring and orange peel.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Pack into Star and Heart Mold, one flavor at a time.
Refrigerate for 1 to 4 hours.

title: layered mexican nachos
