directions: Brown chuck in skillet, drain. Add 1/2 c salsa and taco seasoning mix. In casserole dish, layer tortilla chips, 1/2 ground chuck, chopped tomatoes and shredded cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 400° until cheese melts. Top with sour cream, salsa, and guacamole.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Whip together and pour
into crust.
Chill at least two hours.

title: pineapple ball
directions: Drain juice from crushed pineapple.
Have cream cheese at room temperature, then work pineapple into the cream cheese with a fork.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts on wax paper. Chill overnight and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with shortening, sugar and egg.
Add nuts. Roll on wax paper and flatten into 4 slabs.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Slice at an angle and bake 5 minutes on a greased cookie sheet at 375°.

title: hawaiian crush
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until mixture is smooth.
Yield:
1 quart.

title: curried goat and rice
directions: Put goat meat into a bowl with curry, pepper, salt, m.s.g., scallion and garlic. Rub together for 1 minute, then leave for 30 minutes to marinate.

title: chicken murphy(in the microwave)
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce, wine, oregano, basil and potato in microwave dish.
Cover and cook on Medium-high for 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and spoon sauce over top.
Cover and cook about 12 minutes on Medium-high or until all ingredients are tender.
Remove from microwave several times while cooking and rearrange ingredients to ensure even cooking.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend soft cream cheese and 2 Tbsp. oleo until smooth. Combine all remaining ingredients except bread crumbs, mix well. Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles, seal perforations. Spoon 1/2 c. mixture into center of each.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center and seal edges.
Brush tops with 1 Tbsp. melted oleo and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 - 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli in
small
amount of water for 2 minutes. Drain. Butter a 6 x 9-inch glass dish.
Layer chopped broccoli, chopped pepper and	chopped onion in bottom of dish.
Beat together
the next
ingredients
until
smooth.
Pour	over broccoli mixture. Add cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares to serve.

title: dried beef cream cheese spread
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in a lightly greased baking dish. Cover with sour cream.
Sprinkle with sour cream.
Sprinkle with bacon and top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by directions.
Add other ingredients.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Brown	meat;
drain.
Stir
in tomato sauce and seasoning
mix;	simmer	5
minutes.
Unroll dough. Press into bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover
crust
with	meat mixture.
Top with processed cheese spread.
Continue baking until processed cheese spread begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients. Serve with sour cream, if desired.	Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sun-up punch
directions: Combine the juices and sugar.
Chill several hours.
Just before serving, place ice and juices in punch bowl.
Resting bottles on rim, carefully pour in ginger ale and carbonated water. Makes 10 cups.

title: coleslaw medley
directions: In a large bowl, combine the coleslaw mix, romaine and onion. In a jar with a tight- fitting lid, combine the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and contents of seasoning packet from noodles; shake well. Break noodles into small pieces. Sprinkle noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds over salad; mix well. Drizzle with dressing and toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: white cake
directions: Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix in egg whites and add cold water.
Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) round layer pans. Bake in moderate oven (325° to 350°) for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine garlic, soy sauce and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Add chicken wings.
Cover and cook over high heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked potatoes with a crunch
directions: Mix paprika, salt and crumbs together.
Dip raw potatoes first in margarine, then in crumbs.
Do each piece twice.
Put in casserole and pour remaining margarine and crumbs over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; heat until boiling. Remove from heat and add the oats, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by the teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart on waxed paper.
Cool and eat.
Makes a lot.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a medium sized bowl.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Stir butter in hot water in a separate bowl.
When water has cooled to lukewarm, add yeast and let develop 5 minutes.
Add yeast mixture to bowl with flour mixture. Mix until a dough forms that leaves sides of bowl.
It will be somewhat sticky.
Make a ball of the dough.
Let rise in oiled bowl for 45 minutes or until doubled.
Shape by pulling and rolling on sheet.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes, tossed in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and spread in 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat together 3/4 cup margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cookie mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Combine Jell-O, boiling water and fruit.
Chill until it begins to set. Pour over mixture in pan.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: dream cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients (except powdered sugar) and add to creamed mixture. Drop by scant teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes until light brown.
While warm, roll or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate covered coconut balls
directions: Mix coconut, milk, & vanilla with powdered sugar & nuts. Roll in small balls. Melt wax & chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate mixture. Then drop on wax paper to cool.

title: rolls
directions: In one bowl, dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in lukewarm water. In another bowl, dissolve Crisco in hot water. Set both bowls aside to cool.
Mix together.
Add eggs and enough flour to make soft dough, about 6 cups.
Leave out about 2 hours or place in refrigerator to rise. Bake at 450°.

title: hearty chowder
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: low-fat au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; put in glass casserole dish.
Pour golden mushroom soup over beans.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grandpap's favorite ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and molasses. Add dry ingredients and water. Drop and flatten with glass.
Bake about 8 minutes at 400°.

title: jeanette's squash bisque
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Add vegetables, broth, and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Pour into blender - fill blender half full at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Pour back into pot.
Add half and half.
Head - Do NOT boil.
Add croutons if desired.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem of peppers. Remove all seeds and membranes. Wash inside out. Cook pepper in boiling, salted water 5 minutes and drain. Cook hamburger and onion together. Drain. Combine to this the rice, large tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Heat together thoroughly. Salt insides of peppers and stuff each pepper with hamburger mixture. Stand upright in ungreased baking dish and pour remaining sauce over tops of peppers. Cover. Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover. Add cheeses and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Steam veggies.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Add to veggies.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Put stuffing mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 for top.
Put veggies on top. Sprinkle top with reserved topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: doughnut drops
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Drop by spoonful until brown and done.
Roll in sugar mixed with little cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: In a bowl, combine whole cranberries, pecans, mixed fruit, dates, raisins and orange peel with 1/4 c. flour and mix to coat; set aside.
In another bowl, combine sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and remaining flour; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, then mix in orange juice, shortening and water.
Add the flour mixture and stir until just combined.
Fold in the cranberry mixture.
Spoon into 3 greased and waxed paper lined 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60-65 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in the pans and then remove to wire racks.
Remove waxed paper and let cool completely on the racks.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, place the bread and sprinkle the sausage over it.
Beat eggs, salt and half and half.
Pour over the bread and sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over the mixture.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Leftovers reheat well in the microwave.

title: escarole and beans
directions: Place oil in pan along with escarole, salt, pepper, garlic and red pepper.
Stir together, cover and cook over low heat.
Escarole will wilt and cook down.
Drain beans well!!
Add to escarole and stir together; adjust seasoning.
Heat until beans are warmed.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil over medium heat and saute onion, green onions, parsley and bell pepper until the onions are clear. Stir in tomato sauce and garlic and continue cooking until the tomato sauce starts to boil.
Stir in rice and mix well, then add the water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, hot sauce and shrimp. Continue cooking on medium heat, stirring occasionally to prevent rice from sticking.
After the water has disappeared from the top, reduce the heat to low, cover tightly and let steam undisturbed for at least 45 minutes.
Stir well before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: venison sausage
directions: Cut deer and pork into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a large dishpan.
Grind together with a large chopper plate.
Grind second time with a smaller chopper plate.
Freeze and use within 3 months.

title: chicken-n-noodles
directions: Mix soup, broth and chicken.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: crock-pot cheesey potatoes
directions: Depending on size of crock-pot as to the amount of potatoes used and water.
Layer potatoes, onion, cheese.
Alternate; on top of mixture, pour soups and paprika.
Cook on high 2 hours and turn to low setting 2 to 3 hours depending on tenderness of potatoes.

title: wild rice stuffing
directions: Prepare wild rice mix according to directions; set aside. Break sausage into pieces; brown in small skillet.
Remove sausage and pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the sausage drippings from the skillet.
Saute celery and onion in dripping until crisp-tender.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: micro chocolate fudge
directions: In large glass measuring cup, combine chips and milk. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla extract.
Spread evenly into 8 x 8-inch foil-lined pan.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt chocolate on low heat in double boiler.
Add oil and pecans, stirring constantly, until chocolate has melted and oil and nuts have been mixed.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place marshmallows side by side, closely, to cover chocolate.
Pour remainder of chocolate over marshmallows, spreading evenly.
Refrigerate until hard.
Cut into 16 pieces.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove and discard stems from spinach. Tear into bite size pieces.
Place in salad bowl. Add mushrooms and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add Dijonnaise, lemon juice and bacon bits.
Toss thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stir-fried chicken with cashews and green onion
directions: Mix together egg white, the 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce in a small bowl.
Add chicken.
Stir to coat all pieces.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease pans.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and add dry ingredients.
Mix well and add nuts and bananas.
Pour in bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fran's french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; shake well and serve.
May be stored in refrigerator for later use.

title: grannie turner's ole style dressing
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Put plenty of stock in mixture. Taste until it suits your taste.
When the dressing is in the pan, drizzle a little bacon grease on top.
You have to keep tasting all along to make sure it's seasoned right.
Don't forget to cut up the chicken and put it in the mixture.
If you would like, you could saute the celery and onion until they are tender, then it won't take as long to cook.

title: goodie bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top.

title: souffle
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put in bread (cut in bite size pieces).
Saute sliced mushrooms and saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle ham over bread.
Put mushroom mixture over ham.
Mix Cheddar cheese with 1 tablespoon flour.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Beat eggs with dry mustard, garlic salt and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: fat free pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients very smoothly.
Pour in an 8 or 9-inch pie or cake pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Let cool.
Low-fat Cool Whip is good with this.
Shake a little bit of nutmeg on top of the Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine and cover with crushed potato chips.
Add a little dill, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be mixed the night before and refrigerated.
Nice served with mixed fruit salad.

title: delicious cobbler
directions: *Use 2 cans sliced peaches with syrup, 2 packages frozen strawberries with syrup, thawed, 1 large can sweet potatoes with syrup, sliced or 2 large cans of apples with syrup or fresh fruit.

title: lentil soup
directions: Fry bacon in 3-quart saucepan or Dutch oven until limp; drain on paper towels.
Add onion, carrot, celery and garlic to bacon fat.
Cook and stir over medium heat until celery is tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in bacon, 4 cups water, the lentils, bouillon cube, parsley, salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until soup thickens, about 1 hour. Stir in tomatoes (with liquid) and 1 cup water.
Simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (about 1 1/2 cups each).

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa.
Cream together with margarine and eggs. Beat well.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
When done, spread marshmallow cream over hot cake.
Let cool, then frost.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Place cut up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bring broth and soup to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter.
Add to flour and then add milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at
400° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: german baked beans(yankee magazine)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in butter.
Combine with other ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bulgur meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, slightly beat egg white.
Stir in milk, oats, uncooked bulgur, onion salt, sage and pepper. Add beef; mix well. Shape mixture into loaf in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until meat is well done.
Transfer meat to platter. Brush top with preserves or marmalade.
Slice to serve.
Also serve baby carrots and tossed salad. Serves 4.
Contains 248 calories.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; saute onions and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, blending well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide cheese mixture in half.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: melange of sprouts salad
directions: In a pretty glass bowl, mix celery, cucumber, onions and tomatoes with 1/2 cup dressing.
Cover and chill for at least 15 minutes.
Just before serving, arrange bean sprouts around outer edge of salad, then lentil sprouts, and last, the alfalfa sprouts in the center.

title: hot fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt the butter in water. Add chocolate, sugar, corn syrup and salt. Cook 5 minutes. Add vanilla. Remove from heat.
Makes excellent ice cream topping.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In medium bowl, mix flour, meal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
With fork, stir in milk, oil and egg, just until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in an unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: In a large kettle, combine gelatin with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Fold in all ingredients, except sour cream. Turn half of mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Evenly spread sour cream over top.
Gently spoon remainder of mixture (which has been kept at room temperature) over cream.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Add peanut butter and beat until smooth.
Fold in 1 container Cool Whip. Place mixture into pie shell and top with the other Cool Whip.
A chocolate, graham cracker or Nilla wafer pie crust can be used.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Stir in saucepan milk, sugar and salt.
Cook on low heat until boils.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and chocolate pieces.
Stir until melted. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 36 squares.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Combine chocolate, milk and margarine in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for one minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: peanut butter cookies(yields 3 dozen)
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fast and easy when you need cookies in a hurry!

title: shoe peg casserole
directions: Combine onion, celery, Cheddar cheese, corn, green beans, green pepper, soup and sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs in bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle over casserole. Microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add water and cook until thick. Add jello.
Stir and cool.

title: camper's doughboys
directions: Peel approximately 6
inches
of bark from large end of green hardwood stick,
approximately
to	2
inches in diameter and approximately 4 foot in length, and round off the end of the stick.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Put first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until rice is done.
Pour in 2 eggs slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook 2-3 minutes longer.
Add vanilla.

title: greek rice pudding 2(rizogalo)
directions: Combine milk, rice and sugar in large pan.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling for 45 minutes.
Add lemon peel last 10 minutes of boiling time.
Remove from heat.
Beat 4 egg yolks. Add slightly cooled liquid from rice mixture into egg yolks, beating continuously.
When bowl is full, pour egg-milk liquid back into rice, stirring constantly.
If pudding appears too thin, bring to 2 quick boils.

title: spiced tea(good for holidays)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use according to strength desired in cup of hot water.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Stir together and freeze.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar, molasses and egg substitute.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased (use Pam) cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: bolgogie:  korean shish kabob
directions: Dice garlic and onion.
Place in bowl and add all other ingredients. Cut steak into 1-inch square cubes into bowl of the mixture.
Marinate 4 hours
or more. Alternate on skewers the marinated steak cubes, pieces of green or red pepper, squares of onion, cherry tomatoes and 1/2 mushrooms.
Grill over charcoal fire 10 to 15 minutes.

title: happy hippo's honey hermits
directions: Put peanut butter in a cup.
Add honey.
Add powdered milk. Add crispy rice cereal.
Stir well.
Roll into balls.
Place on a tray or cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until set.

title: polly cracker cake
directions: Crush
crackers well and mix together with 1 cup sugar, baking powder
and
pecans.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add cream
of tartar and 1 cup sugar.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold egg whites into dry mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 15-inch
pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and then
add
topping. Mix
Cool
Whip,
pineapple
and coconut; spread
over cake. Seven Minute Frosting is also good on this cake.

title: pineapple upside cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in an ovenproof skillet or 9-inch cake pan.
Stir in brown sugar over low heat until it dissolves.
Remove from heat; add pineapple juice. Arrange pineapple rings with a cherry in the center in 1 layer; set aside.
Melt remaining 8 tablespoons butter; remove from heat. Stir in milk and egg; beat well.

title: easy bread and butter pickles
directions: Stir and pour over cukes and onions.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Put in large casserole dish and top with 2 cups of crushed corn flakes, combine with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Spread over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May be frozen ahead.
Add topping before baking.

title: meatballs
directions: Make meatballs desired size.
Place in baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) and set aside until sauce is heated.

title: quick and easy potatoes(great for a crowd)
directions: Slice and layer potatoes in a greased (1/4 inch) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and top with pats of butter. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° until all potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: hormel sausage delight
directions: Melt jelly and mustard in crock-pot together. Add sausage and let simmer until the sausage is hot.

title: fruit-nut sandwich spread
directions: Put cottage cheese and lemon juice in a blender until smooth. Add raisins and pineapple; blend just until fruit is finely chopped.
Scrape mixture into a bowl.
Stir in nuts.
Cover and keep cold until serving.
May be used on crackers, bread slices or sandwiches.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add chilies, olives, chili powder, cumin, red pepper, cilantro and ketchup.
Set aside.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil peeled sweet potatoes for 15 minutes.
Reserve 1 cup liquid.
Combine liquid with next 5 ingredients and boil 5 minutes, remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Line baking dish with sliced cooked sweet potatoes and pour mixture over all.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy jello parfaits
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and enough ice cubes to make one cup.
Add to gelatin; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice!
Stir in yogurt and vanilla.
Pour into 4 or 5 individual parfait glasses. Optional:
Alternate with corresponding fruit to flavor of Jell-O. Refrigerate until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish, if desired. Makes 2 1/2 cups.
From Kraft General Foods, Inc.

title: cheri's angel fruit cake
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces and place in a sheet cake pan.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar.
In another bowl, mix 3 packages of Dream Whip as directed on package.
Mix with cream cheese mixture.
Pour over cake, then add cherry pie filling or fresh fruit.
Pour over top.
Chill.
Spoon out to serve.

title: pineapple chicken salad
directions: Place pineapple with juice in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Drain and toss small amount of mayonnaise with ingredients.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: strudel(retes)
directions: Add all ingredients.
Add more water, if necessary, to make a soft dough.
Knead dough well and let set. Work with beating motion with hands until smooth, elastic and until bubbles appear in dough.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Cover and let rest 30 minutes.

title: east indian potato balls
directions: Boil the potatoes and peel and mash.
Add salt, sugar, lime juice and ginger.
Dip a piece of bread in the buttermilk and press flat.
Pat some parsley around a doughnut-hole sized piece of potato mixture and lay on the bread (that is buttermilk side down).
Roll the bread into a ball around the potato mixture and seal.
Fry in hot oil in a shallow pan until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: micro potatoes parmesan
directions: Melt margarine in shallow 9-inch dish in microwave oven.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic.
Toss.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and place in microwave oven on Full power for 5 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil in microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Stir together with peanuts and corn flakes.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Refrigerate.

title: yummy onion potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with French fried onion rings and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: pumpkin cake squares
directions: Grease and flour pan.
This has to be mixed in three bowls. Reserve 1 cup yellow cake mix.
Mix rest of cake mix, 1/2 cup melted margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8 x 11-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry puffs
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Chop cherries.
Add liquid, 1/2 cup sugar and tapioca.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Beat egg whites, dash of salt and cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat to stiff peaks.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon color.
Fold yolks into whites.
Sift flour over and pour cherry mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour batter over.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and simmer 45 minutes or until mixture starts to thicken.
Beat egg in a measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir eggs and water rapidly into rice mixture.
Add raisins, if desired.
Pour in square dish, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on package.
When done, pierce.
While still hot, pour Dairy Sweet over top.
Smooth over cake.
Let cool.
Spread with pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Prepare vegetables and layer in bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before stirring and serving.

title: peanut butter bon bons
directions: In a large bowl, beat peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and salt until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk and then sugar until smooth. Shape into 1 inch balls and place on a baking sheet.
Chill until firm.
Dip bon bons in melted chocolate using a toothpick.
Place on baking sheets lined with wax paper and chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator or room temperature. Makes 1 1/2 doz.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Put chicken in baking pan and brush both sides with seasoned butter.
Sprinkle with oregano leaves.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, until chicken is done.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with nuts and coconut.
Prepare cake mix according to directions. Pour into pan over nuts and coconut.
Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar; mix well and spoon over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to a rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, beating until smooth.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Cool completely.
Fill with pudding. Makes about 5 dozen.
You can sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach completely.
Mix all ingredients and chill 3 hours.

title: creamy blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended and creamy. Chill and serve over tossed salad.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream 2 cubes butter, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add and mix eggs and vanilla.
Add and mix flour, nuts and coconut. Spread into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread hot cake immediately (gently) with 1 jar marshmallow cream.

title: ruffles cookies
directions: Cream butter, Mazola and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted flour and Ruffles potato chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato cake
directions: Combine potatoes and milk in a bowl.
Mix well.
Cream butter and sugar in a bowl; add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Blend in chocolate.
Add potato mixture; mix well.
Sift in flour, baking powder and spices.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 16 servings.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Stir in flour and pecans. Shape into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake until brown or about 30 minutes at 300°. While hot, roll puffs in powdered sugar. When cold, roll again. Yields 3 dozen.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Heat raisins and apple juice concentrate in a saucepan until raisins are soft (approximately 3 minutes).
Pour raisins into a blender and puree.
Add banana, oil, vanilla, applesauce and egg to blender and blend together.

title: mcintosh sandwich
directions: Butter slices of bread.
Cover with slices of unpeeled thinly sliced apples. Dot with butter. Spread with ham.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put in hot oven for 3 to 4 minutes until butter melts and sandwich is hot. Place Swiss cheese on top and put under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve open faced while hot. Add corn chips for a delicious meal.
Serves 4.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Wash spinach; drain.
Layer spinach, mandarin oranges and almonds on individual salad plates.
Top with desired amount of dressing.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken breast halves and water to cover in a medium saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is done; drain well.
Remove chicken from bone and coarsely chop chicken.
Place coarsely chopped chicken in a 1-quart casserole, coated with vegetable cooking spray, and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread mix according to package.
Pour into greased shallow pan.
Cook onion in butter until soft.
Sprinkle onion mixture and celery seed on batter.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Great served with hot fish and green salad.

title: party potatoes casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes; mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup margarine and 1 cup corn flake crumbs.
Place in a long shallow greased dish.
Potatoes should be no more than 1 1/2 to 2 inches deep. Make topping of melted margarine and corn flake crumbs.
Spread over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all above and pour into 2 1/2 to 3 quart casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 16.
Can be divided and frozen, but do not cook before freezing.

title: "robert's" beefaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Brown onion and ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together the cooked macaroni, beef and onion, tomato soup and tomatoes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(If glass baking dish is used, reduce heat to 325°.)
Add cheese evenly on top; bake another 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, dump pie filling (smooth out).
Dump crushed pineapple (smooth out).
Dump box of dry cake mix (smooth out).
Top with nuts and drizzle top with margarine.
Bake until gold and bubbly (approximately 45 minutes).

title: gazpacho with shrimp
directions: In food processor or blender, mince the garlic and parsley. Add the cucumber, green pepper and scallions and coarsely chop. Turn the mixture into a large serving bowl and stir in the shrimp, vegetable juice, vinegar, salt, black pepper and cumin.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: dilly macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain well.
Cool. Combine macaroni, celery, red pepper, carrot and parsley.
Blend together mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and dill weed.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Toss lightly.
Cover and chill well.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: In a large saucepan melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In a separate container combine flour, salt and peanuts.
Stir to coat peanuts. Add gradually (but quickly) to saucepan ingredients.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes (or until cake tester comes out clean). Spread marshmallows over warm cake.
Yields approximately 15 slices.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Use 3 bowls for the egg, flour and milk.
Put each slice in flour, then egg mixture, then flour.
Do this until all eggplant is coated.
Use a large frying pan or wok. Fill halfway with olive oil.
Fry each piece until golden brown. Put on a plate with a paper towel.
Take a large casserole and put sauce on bottom.
Layer eggplant, next sauce, then cheese.
Do this until pan is full.
Put last layer of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Serve and enjoy.
Great leftover.
Heat in microwave.

title: chicken au gratin casserole
directions: Place beans and chicken in casserole.
Mix soup and water; bring to a boil and pour over chicken mixture.
Season to taste. Combine bread cubes, margarine and cheese.
Toss lightly and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Whip until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk while blending.
Be sure cream cheese and milk are blended well then add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend mixture until smooth.
Pour into choice of crust.
Chill two hours.
Garnish top of pie with Cherry Pie Filling.
Chill. Serves 6 - 8.

title: nita's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa in large bowl.
Bring oleo and water to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and salt to mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: shaker nut bread
directions: Mix sifted dry ingredients and nuts together.
Combine egg, applesauce and oil.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour mixture into 5 x 9-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: clam scallop
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in a greased Bundt or angel food cake pan. Sprinkle dry butterscotch pudding mix over the rolls.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook shells in boiling water according to package directions. Drain.
Meanwhile, beat egg in a bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, ham, pepperoni, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 11 1/2 x 7 3/4-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Now spoon about 2 tablespoons of cottage cheese mixture into each shell.
Arrange in baking dish in a single layer.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Cover and microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High, rotating dish 1/4 turn 3 times until bubbly.

title: banana upside-down cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons water; stir until mixture resembles damp sand. Melt over high heat until sugar caramelizes; when caramel is dark amber, add 1/2 stick butter.
Stir. Pour into 8-inch pan (square). Arrange bananas, cut lengthwise and then crosswise, cut side down in pan.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth. Add sugar and mix well. Add vanilla and beat well (until smooth). Spread on cake. Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: caramel coconut cream cheese pie
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet; add coconut and nuts and toast until brown.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk; mix until smooth and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 cup cream cheese mixture into each pie crust.
Drizzle on caramel topping; sprinkle toasted coconut and nuts on top and repeat each layer. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: grilled trout a la bill
directions: Start with a cleaned up trout!
Marinate in vinaigrette for 30 to 45 minutes, no longer or you'll lose the flavor!
Grill over high heat on gas grill for 15 minutes, turning once.
Fish is done when it flakes on piercing with a fork.

title: roast beef
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Add wine and beef stock; mix. Add garlic, onions and pepper.
Roast at 325° for approximately 90 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Whip 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, margarine, egg, salt and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Whip the cream and 1/2 tablespoon powdered sugar. Fold in pineapple and nuts. Top pie with mixture and place in refrigerator.
This recipe is more economical if made in lots of three.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until light.
Add milk, then melted butter and extract.
Sift flour and add baking powder.
Add liquid mixture to them and beat well.
Bake about 45 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.

title: hawaiian pineapple banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts.

title: wild rice almond salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to large bowl.
Stir in celery and carrots while rice is still hot.
Saute almonds in olive oil until lightly browned.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over rice and vegetable mixture.
Toss until well blended.
Cover and chill.
To serve, line a bowl with leaf lettuce.
Spoon in rice mixture.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and blend. Add dry ingredients, mix and chill briefly.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: You will need a ring pan.

title: earnestine's fruit salad
directions: Mix the instant pudding with juice from fruit.
Pour over mixed fruit and chill.

title: yellow raisin cake
directions: Put raisins in 2 cups hot water to soak.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty yellow cake mix into large mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Break eggs into a cup and beat well.
Add to mix and stir. Add the oil and vanilla; mix well.
Wash raisins and add to mix. Bake in large greased loaf pan for 35 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean.

title: dream-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water, add 7-UP and rest of ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: daddy's favorite carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with mixer after each.
Stir in carrots.
Sift next 4 dry ingredients together.
Blend into batter, mixing well. Pour into 3 greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Spread between layers and over tops and sides of cake.
Garnish with pecans.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add berries. Place in refrigerator and let thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break cake into small pieces and alternate cake and Jell-O mixture in a large bowl.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate fudge candy *
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and squares of chocolate in saucepan and cook until forms firm ball in water.
Remove from heat and mix in bowl with marshmallows, semi-chocolate bits and pecans. Beat and pour in wax paper lined pan.
Cut in squares as desired.

title: ranch chicken salad
directions: Toss salad greens with chicken and vegetables in a large salad bowl.
Add dressing and barbecue sauce.
Mix lightly. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bess truman's ozark pudding
directions: Beat together egg and sugar until thoroughly blended and smooth.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into the egg-sugar mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts, chopped apple and vanilla extract.
Turn into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend the flour mixture into the shortening and sugar.
Add the mincemeat, eggs (beaten), tomato soup and chopped nuts.
Blend together well.
Pour into Bundt pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Pour in cocktail with juice. Add beaten eggs.
Mix and pour in 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, nuts (pecans) and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Roll chicken in seasoned flour and brown in oil.
Remove chicken.
Stir in soup, onion, seasonings and water into drippings. Cook and stir to boil, mixing soup thoroughly.
Spread uncooked rice in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Pour two-thirds of soup mixture over rice and stir to moisten.
Top rice mixture with chicken and pour rest of soup over chicken.
Bake, covered with foil, at 375° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put on a greased baking sheet pan like ordinary cookies.
Bake for about 15 minutes.
Put marshmallow cream between 2 cookies and Whooppee what a pie.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: crab spread
directions: Drain can of crab.
Drain and chop water chestnuts and add to crab.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Serve with crackers.

title: mushrooms florentine *
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Slice off stems.
Saute stems and caps until brown.
Line shallow 10-inch casserole with spinach that has been seasoned with salt, onion and melted butter. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Arrange mushrooms over the spinach. Season with garlic salt.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: betty's buttermilk pudding
directions: Mix pudding with buttermilk in large bowl.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Stir in fruits and chill.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and noodles.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper. Cool and serve.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops; place in flat baking dish.
Mix the bread crumbs, onion, margarine, water and sage; put mound of dressing on each pork chop.
Blend the soup with 1/3 can water; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tasty dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add melted butter.
Add salt and most of the flour.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and satiny.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth, adding a little flour if necessary.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a long loaf.
Cut each loaf into 6 even pieces.
Shape into oblong rolls.

title: aunt camille's chinese chews
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; beat well.	Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Bake	in
shallow, greased pan at 350°, about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.	Cut in squares.

title: apricot baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread mixture over chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Turn dish after 10 minutes.

title: remembrance strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin.
Pour over strawberries; mix well.
Pour into pie shell; refrigerate until set.
Spread Cool Whip over top.

title: sirloin tips with mushrooms
directions: Coat a wide skillet with nonstick spray.
Brown meat.
Add garlic.
As pieces brown, remove and place in a casserole dish with a lid.
Add 1/4 cup wine to skillet.
Saute mushrooms and add to meat.
Cover.
Bake slowly at 275° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: tuna, tomato and olives
directions: In a serving bowl, mix tuna, olives, oregano, lemon zest, pepper and olive oil, leaving tuna in large chunks.
Cook pasta as label directs until al dente.
Add 1/3 cup pasta water to tuna mixture.
Mix gently. Drain pasta and add.
Toss.
Sprinkle with tomato.
Serve with lemon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion with a hand chopper. Add cheese and bacon bits. In a separate bowl, mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar. Stir mixture into vegetables. Season to taste. Refrigerate.

title: napoli casserole
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Add 1/2 cup cheese; stir until melted.
Remove sausage from casing and cut into pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Add zucchini and onion.
Cook until tender and drain.
Stir in white sauce, noodles and tomatoes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: mexican cheese puffs
directions: Combine water and butter in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once.
Stir until it makes a smooth ball.
Remove from heat and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool on rack.

title: chocolate raspberry cheese cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and press onto the bottom of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: roast meat loaf
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients together and mold in center.
Place around it slices of potatoes, onions and carrots.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and parsley on top.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup and juice from the asparagus together.
Spread asparagus on bottom of casserole dish.
Slice eggs on top of asparagus.
Pour soup mixture over eggs.
Sprinkle grated cheese on soup mixture.
Put bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb with flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Put into a pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Meanwhile, mix the cream cheese, eggs and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over hot rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix sour cream, vanilla and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour over hot pie. Chill before serving.

title: rigatoni salad
directions: Cook and drain rigatoni.
While still warm add oil and mix well to coat the rigatoni.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles per package directions and cool.
Chop green pepper and sea legs; add to noodles.
Season with Old Bay.
Pour Catalina over noodles and mix well.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: nut horns
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt; add Crisco and margarine.
Work in as for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in milk; add beaten egg yolks to flour.
Mix this just long enough for the dough to stay in a ball (do not over work).
Chill overnight.
Divide, roll out in sections and use powdered sugar to roll on.
Cut in squares; place teaspoon of filling in each square and roll.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Chop artichoke hearts in food processor or finely by hand; set aside.
Saute the onion and garlic in water until tender; set aside.
In small bowl, beat egg and egg whites until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing until well combined.
Transfer mixture into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.
Yields 25 squares.
These are great warm, room temperature or even reheated.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, baking in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook cake in pan 15 minutes, then pick with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: blueberry cottage pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Alternately add flour and milk to sugar mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Add 1 cup blueberries; mix.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: just dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into greased 8-inch pan (Pam is good to use).
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over the top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Can be served warm or cold, with or without Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Cut in shortening. Add vinegar and water until dough holds together. Shape into 2 balls. Refrigerate; roll out. Place into pie pans. Brush top with egg white.
Can be used with any pie filling.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Whisk all ingredients together in a large bowl. Add water to desired consistency. Adjust amount of sugar to preference.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Cream well.
Mix in flour and blend.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add milk, lemon juice and rind.
Blend in mixture until smooth.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff but
not dry. Fold into mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish (9-inch square or 6 x 9-inch).
Place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is slightly brown.
Let cool.
Cake will rise to top and pudding to the bottom.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together. Do not beat: cooking oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add apples and nuts. Mix in other bowl flour, salt, cinnamon and soda. Stir into apple mixture. Dough will be thick. Add raisins if you like. Bake at 350 degrees
for 1 hr. Best baked in a bundt pan. Cool 10 minutes in pan. Turn out on rack until cool.

title: plenty more in kitchen casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef and onion. Add the rest of the ingredients, except the cooked macaroni. Simmer for 10 minutes, then add the cooked macaroni and bake 1 hour in greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: homemade beef stick
directions: Mix as for meat loaf.
Mold into two logs.
Form and shape with wax paper or hands.
Bake on rack in an open pan at 140° for hours or at 150° for 8 hours.
May be frozen after baking.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams and combine with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill to blend flavors.
Makes one cup.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Sweeten strawberries as desired.
Mix strawberries and jello over medium-low heat until jello is dissolved (do not add water). In medium bowl, mix together the pudding and milk.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and Cool Whip.
Lay vanilla wafers in bottom of 9 x 11-inch serving dish.
Spread pudding mixture on top of wafers.
Pour strawberries over pudding.
Top with sour cream mixture.

title: mexicali rice
directions: Cook peppers and onions until tender.
Add corn, salsa and broth.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice, cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Add cheese, fluff with fork.
Serve with beef filled tostadas.
Enjoy!!

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl and make a well in the center.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into dry ingredients. Stir just enough to dampen all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and sugared loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 25 minutes in pan.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
With pastry brush, grease well muffin pan cups.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl with fork, beat egg slightly, then stir milk, salad oil and bananas into beaten egg.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture and with spoon stir just until flour is moistened. Add nuts, if desired; stir briefly.
(Avoid overmixing; batter should be lumpy.)
Spoon batter into muffin pan.
Wipe pan clean of any spills.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes for 12 muffin pan, 30 to 35 minutes for 6 muffin pan, until golden and tester comes out clean and dry.
Remove immediately.
Serve at once.
Store in airtight container.

title: england spot-of-pizzas
directions: Split and crisply toast English muffins.
Mix catsup, oregano, vinegar, onion powder, sugar and pepper. Spread 1/4 of each muffin half. Top each with 1/4 of the pepperoni.
Place 1 tablespoon Mozzarella on each muffin half. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Pop into oven about 300° until cheese is melted or pop into microwave on High (100%) until cheese is melted.
Makes 16 servings.

title: smokey salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon.
Beat cream cheese with lemon juice, milk and dill weed in mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in salmon and green onions until thoroughly combined.
Season with liquid smoke to taste.
Chill several hours before serving to allow flavors to blend.
To serve, spread on crackers and French bread round. Makes 25 servings, about 3 1/2 cups.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar; cut in butter. Press into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: beef wellington
directions: Mix beef, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, egg, 1/4 cup gravy and bread crumbs.
Pat into loaf and place in a shallow pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes in large flat dish.
Mix next seven ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over top (in addition to 2 cups).
Melt another 1/4 to 1/2 cup oleo and pour over top of potato casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 deep pie plates.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in dish.
Top with chilies.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place vegetables in a greased casserole dish in alternate layers.
Add milk, seasonings and cheese.
Cover dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scoffield
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and chill several hours before serving.
Cut tomatoes in half. Serve in a bowl and use a spoon to drink
the
juice.
(The
juice
is as good as the tomatoes.)

title: tomato salsa
directions: Peel and core tomatoes, cut into quarters. Do not add water. Chop onions and peppers.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook about 2 hours, stirring often to keep from sticking.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In morning, change water and parboil them for 15 minutes with baking soda.
Drain beans and rinse with cold water.
Dice salt pork rind in 1-inch squares.
Place in bottom of bean pot.
Add whole onion.
Add beans.
Mix remaining ingredients with hot water.
Add to pot.
Beans should be covered with liquid.
Add small amount of water, if necessary.
Bake for 6 hours at 300°.

title: ruffage vegetable soup
directions: Cover, lower heat and simmer until vegetables are cooked but crisp.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 heaping teaspoonful per cup of boiling water.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch flavored morsels.
Drop by level measuring tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crisper cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen (3-inch) cookies.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown (about 25 minutes, depending on oven).
Cut in 2 x 1-inch squares.
Makes 4 dozen.
Can be frozen.
Reheat in oven, not microwave.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown beef.
Add finely chopped onions, including blades, and saute.
Add finely chopped carrot, pepper and cabbage.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring often.
Add cooked rice and mix.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers in pan.
Cover with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt; mix well.
Let soak 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Drain well. Mix 1/2 cup white vinegar and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir real good. Pack cucumbers in plastic freezer cartons.
Pour liquid mixture over.
Put in freezer and freeze.
Will last in freezer a long time.
To eat, thaw.

title: turkey or chicken marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate meat overnight in mixture.
Drain meat and grill over charcoal or gas grill.
Leftover marinade may be refrigerated and used later.

title: stuffed baked potatoes with horseradish cream
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pierce potatoes several times with a fork.
Place on oven rack; bake until crisp outside and cooked through about 1 hour.
Transfer to a small baking sheet; cool 5 minutes.
Cut off top third of potatoes.
Scoop potato from bottoms into large bowl, leaving 1/4-inch thick shell.
Scoop potato from tops and add to same bowl; discard tops.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients, then slowly add the dry ingredients to the liquid bowl.
Mix well.
Flour and grease loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: quick butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish. Make batter using sugar, milk and flour. Pour this over the oleo. Do not stir. Pour sweetened peaches over batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine
flour,
salt and pepper; use to coat meat.
In Dutch oven,
brown
meat	in
hot Crisco; add soup, water and onions. Cover
and	bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add carrots and potatoes; bake
for
hour, or until vegetables are tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: old-fashioned dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1 cup chicken broth and oil, stirring well until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and form into a ball.
Roll dough to a 1/16-inch thickness.
Cut into 5 x 1-inch strips.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until dumplings are tender.
Makes 16 servings (that's what the cookbook says it must be mouse size servings).
Can add poultry seasoning, sage and onion to taste.

title: zucchini-sour cream casserole
directions: Slice zucchini horizontally; simmer, covered, in small amount of water for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine sour cream, butter, 3 tablespoonfuls cheese and salt.
Stir over hot water in double boiler until cheese melts.
Stir in egg yolk and onion.
Add all this to zucchini; turn into buttered 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion.
Add beans, syrup and catsup. Pour into a casserole and bake for about 30 minutes.

title: pasta, peppers and beans
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Cut the onion into thin slices and the peppers into bite-size pieces.
In large skillet, warm 2 tablespoons of oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute 5 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and almond bark in large pan in 200° oven or use microwave oven.
Mix well.
While still hot, add peanuts and continue stirring until all peanuts are coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool.
Makes a "bunch."

title: broccoli and potato
directions: Sprinkle frozen broccoli with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour boiling water on broccoli in a large bowl.
Cover and let stand 3 minutes; drain.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour salad dressing over broccoli and potatoes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; toss.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cucumber-buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine buttermilk, cucumber, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper in small bowl; mix well.
Cover; chill 30 minutes.
Serve over lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, sweet green peppers, celery, cucumbers or carrots.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hawaiian sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in small amount of vegetable oil.
Add 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer (do not boil) until tender, about 1 hour or less.
Drain pineapple and reserve syrup.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve on hot steamed rice.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Season tails
with
salt
and
pepper; set aside.
Melt butter; add onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery;	cook until tender.
Add tails	and 1 1/2 cups water; boil for 20 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch
in
cup
water; add to mixture.
Add green onion
and parsley; season to taste.	Add Worcestershire and hot sauce; cook 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Combine sugar, oil, eggs and zucchini.
Add vanilla and sifted ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 4 medium pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jennifer's mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Mix soups, water, chilies, milk and taco sauce together well.
Alternate meat, tortillas and soup mixture in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 easily.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package. Add sugar and mix thoroughly. Add cream cheese; beat thoroughly until mixed. Pour into pie shells. Sprinkle with pecans. Top with blueberry filling.

title: speedy veggie wrap-ups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine cheese, broccoli coleslaw and tomato.
Place 1/2 cup mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll tortilla up, folding in ends.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: p-nut butter cereal
directions: Cook over low to medium heat until starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until coated.
Pour into buttered pan. Cut when cool.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: *A mixture of Crisco and margarine is suggested for the cup of shortening.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until frothy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture; mix well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well. Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Carefully remove and reserve rind from melon.
Cut rind into desired shapes or pieces.
Soak overnight in 1 gallon of cold water and lime.
Stir occasionally while soaking.
After soaking, rinse well.
Place rinsed rinds in saucepan and cook in enough water to cover rinds, for 20 minutes.
Drain and soak rinds in an ice bath, changing water and adding ice until cooled.
Remove rinds from ice bath and put in boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain and cool with running water.
Now you are ready to make your syrup.

title: fruit and zucchini bars
directions: Drizzle over warm bar cookies; spread evenly.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Cool well before cutting into bars.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: corn dip
directions: Season to taste with salt, coarse ground pepper and lemon pepper.
Mix well, chill and serve with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: golden butter cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar to mix, Wesson oil and eggs as you go.
Mix in sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.

title: french apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over peeled, sliced apples.
Combine dry ingredients and pour over apples.
Add melted butter, lightly beaten egg, raisins and nuts.
Mix together and then pour into an 8-inch square pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick. Cool and add pecans and bananas.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: baked curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and layer in a large casserole dish.
Melt margarine, brown sugar and curry powder.
Preheat oven to 325°. Pour melted mixture over fruit and bake for 1 hour.

title: easy stromboli
directions: Unroll dough; place on greased cookie sheet.
Press dough into a 12 x 8 rectangle.
Spread sauce on dough to within 2 inches of long side and 1/2 inch on short side.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat soup and soy sauce until smooth.
Mix in beans, pepper and 1/2 cup of onions.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: egg breakfast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break up bread.
Stir in cheese and ham.
Pour eggs, milk and spices that have been beaten well over bread, cheese and ham.
Push any bread that sticks up down with a fork.
Cover with tinfoil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until knife in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and brown and white sugars until creamy. Add salt, soda and eggs. Beat 10 minutes until fluffy. Add flour; mix well. Fold in chocolate chips. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes a double batch.

title: steak oriental
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steak.
Marinate steak at least 6 hours in sauce.
Be sure to turn meat so that it marinates on all sides.
Broil quickly over hot coals or in broiler, about 5 to 7 minutes, on a side for rare meat.

title: soft drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla (or 3/4 tsp. lemon extract).
Mix together flour and baking powder; blend into creamed mixture along with milk.
Drop cookies by heaping teaspoons 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly with fingers; sprinkle with sugar. Press a raisin into the center of each cookie.
Bake 10 minutes in a 375° oven or until cookies brown.
Remove from baking sheet and cook on rack.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in a greased 1-quart casserole; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until the cheese melts.
Pour over potato mixture and stir gently to mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vanilla-orange jello salad
directions: Mix orange Jell-O with boiling water.
Add ice cream, oranges, crushed pineapple and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: polish mashed potato dumplings
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Drop into boiling water with the tip of a teaspoon.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Saute chopped onion in butter until tender.
Drain dumplings well.
Add to butter and onions; salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrot salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine drained pineapple, reserved pineapple juice, carrot, celery or green pepper, lemon peel, lemon juice, sugar, salt and ginger.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco real well; add egg yolks, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in milk and mix well with flour (including salt).
Alternately beat egg whites and fold in last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: double treat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips. Shape into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
(I prefer a glass wrapped in a clean napkin dipped in cold water to flatten.)
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
These are nice and sugary and crunchy if not overbaked.

title: sour cream, banana pudding
directions: Stir pudding mix and milk together following directions on box.
Add sliced bananas, Cool Whip, sour cream and pineapple. Pour into bowl lined with vanilla wafers, adding more as you like and topping with a few more.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Reserve 1 cup flour to dust raisins and nuts.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the Crisco, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together the remaining ingredients.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape teaspoonfuls of dough into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green chili chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook (bake or saute) chicken; shred or cut in small pieces. Saute onion and green chilies in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken.
Blend soup and evaporated milk to make a smooth sauce. Set aside.
In each tortilla, spread diagonally a small portion of the chicken mixture and sauce.
Roll tortilla tightly and arrange in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place tortilla seam side down.
Pour remainder of sauce over tortillas and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° to 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil water and Karo to hard boil stage. Beat 3 egg whites stiff.
Pour sugar mixture over egg whites very slowly while beating. Beat until this loses its gloss. Add nuts and drop on wax paper.

title: lentil garlic soup
directions: Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in water.
Saute garlic, onion and carrots in olive oil in large soup pot.
Add lentils, broth, wine and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: apple brownies
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir lightly.
Add apples.
Beat well. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Can sift powdered sugar on top.

title: chicken and black bean tostizzas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, roll the biscuits to a 5 1/2-inch circle.
Combine salsa, chicken, black beans, cilantro and cumin and spread over the biscuits.
Top with the onions, green pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 24 minutes until brown and the cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream and guacamole.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet baked beans
directions: Mix baked beans, soup, brown sugar, dry onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and bacon; mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and make a loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mandarin triple crown
directions: Boil all ingredients al dente.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil or fry the chicken for 1/2 hour.
Cook rice and then add olives.
Place in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Put chicken on top of rice.
In a bowl blend soup, milk and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 400° uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Combine
sugar,
mustard
seed,
celery seed, turmeric, cider vinegar
and water.
Put on stove and bring to boil the vinegar, sugar
and	spices, then add the drained vegetables. Bring	back to	boil and boil gently 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal. Yield:
approximately 9 pints.

title: copper pennies salad(carrot salad)
directions: Cook peeled, sliced carrots for 10 minutes. Place cooked carrots in large dish with peppers and onions in layers. Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper. Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture. (DO NOT STIR.) Cover lightly and place in refrigerator. Let stand at least 12 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put the oatmeal, margarine and boiling water into a mixing bowl; let stand 20 minutes.
Beat and add sugars and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and lentil pilaf
directions: Saute onion in oil in a skillet until tender.
Add rice and stir until lightly browned.
Add water and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 6 main dish servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into medium baking dish.
Bake 25-30 minutes varying on cookware used.

title: tabulli
directions: Buy macaroni from the grocery store. Boil it in water for 30 minutes, then put the cheese in it.
Stir it up and let it cool for 3 minutes.

title: wayne ginsel's deer camp soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are soft. Add soup, beans and tomatoes.
For thinner soup, add water. Simmer about an hour.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend. Sift flour and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan for about 30 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar until real creamy.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Heat milk with oleo or butter until melted. Add dry ingredients gradually to egg and sugar alternately with hot milk and oleo (butter).
Bake in rectangular cake pan at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into cake.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Dice chicken.
Saute the celery, bell pepper and pimentos in one stick of margarine.
Add soup, milk and grated cheese. Meanwhile, cook spaghetti.
Add spaghetti, chicken and sauce together.
Pour into large baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and heat thoroughly in a moderate oven (350°), for 30 to 45 minutes.
May be topped with cheese and olives, if desired.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix liquid in a cup.
Mix flour, salt and sugar in small bowl. Pour liquid over dry ingredients.
Mix with fork to form ball. Line pie tin.
Press with fork or fingers.
Bake at 425° until lightly brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: walking taco
directions: Layer in the following order in a quiche dish:
Refried beans, Avocados mixed with 1 pint of sour cream, Remaining sour cream less 1 serving spoonful, Cheese, Lettuce, Green onion, Ripe olives, Tomatoes, Remaining dollop of sour cream.
Serve with heavy chips for dipping.

title: citrus shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Place the butter and sugar in the bowl of an electric mixer. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Scrape down sides of the bowl. Beat on high for 3 minutes, until butter is light but not fluffy. Add the zests and liqueur. Beat on high for 30 seconds. Gradually, using low speed, add the flour and salt; mix for 1 minute. Use a rubber spatula to finish mixing the dough.

title: powdered sugar cookies(these must be baked immediately)
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and salt and beat well.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and blend.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend gently into creamed mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Dust pastry cloth with powdered sugar and flour. Roll dough out a small portion at a time to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out with fancy cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: "boiled raisin" cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water until water is absorbed.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Add sifted ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: cherry cheese yum yums
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter and press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and combine with milk, Dream Whip and sugar.
Beat 5 minutes until thick.
Pour on top of crumb crust. Spoon pie filling over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: diana's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Heat margarine and water in saucepan until boiling.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Beat in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour thin batter in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Use with Diana's Chocolate Frosting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together the hash browns, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
