Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with the cornflakes and then drizzle the margarine over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown cracker crumbs in butter.
Press cracker mix onto bottom of pan for crust.
Mix together chicken, sour cream and soup; spoon over crust.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop celery and onion in blender; drain mostly, then add to can of soup.
Heat with additional 1/2 cup water until mixture is smooth.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix in bowl cream cheese, almond extract, 2/3 cup sugar and eggs.
Pour into buttered 10-inch heavy pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Shut off oven; let sit in oven for 20 minutes. Take out cake.

title: honey nut bread
directions: Mix.
Put into greased loaf pan.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peach melba
directions: In saucepan, mash raspberries.
Add jelly and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Blend cornstarch and water; add to jelly mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Let stand until cool. Chill.

title: submarine
directions: Slice buns in half.
Add any of the ingredients to the "bottom half" of the bun.
Cover with top half of bun.
Slice to eat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin, debone and cut into chunks (about 3 cups).
In a saucepan, add spices and onion.
If you buy your chicken already skinned and deboned, you can add it to this and 1 cup water.
When onion is cooked, add soups until mixed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed except use reserved broth in place of the water.
Mix everything together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put into casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; stir only until smooth and moist.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crepes
directions: Combine ingredients together and blend until smooth.
May refrigerate for 1 hour.
(This will allow flour particles to swell and soften so crepes are light in texture.)
Brush the bottom of a nonstick 6-inch pan with oil and place over medium heat.
Pour about 3 tablespoons batter into hot pan and tilt so it covers the pan.
Cook until done and then turn and cook on other side.
Cover crepe with jam, marmalade, etc. and roll up.

title: chesapeake cream crab cakes
directions: Place crabmeat in mixing bowl.
Sprinkle crabmeat with cracker crumbs and mix.
In a small bowl, combine all other ingredients; mix until frothy.
Gently fold mixture with crabmeat, taking care not to break up lumps of crabmeat.
Form into rounded mounds about 1-inch thick up to 3 inches in diameter.
Do not pack too firmly. Fry in deep fat for about 3 minutes or until golden brown. Alternately slip under preheated broiler for about 6 minutes, 3 minutes on either side.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Heat together the juice from the pineapple and enough water to make 1 cup hot liquid.
Add lemon Jell-O and grated cheese.
Chill until thick, then fold in whipped Carnation milk, mayonnaise and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chicken paprika(serves 5)
directions: Saute the onions in the oil.
Stir in paprika and cayenne pepper.
Add the chicken and tomato.
Season with salt.
Add the cauliflower.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
(Do not add water as the chicken will release sufficient liquid for the purpose.)
Blend the sour cream, flour and a little water.
Add to the chicken mixture.
Boil the noodles in salted water.
Heat the butter.
Add the dill.
Pour over noodles.
Serve the chicken mixture over the noodles.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes in water until done.
Drain and mash them.
Beat in enough sugar to make the potatoes as thick as pie dough consistency.
Roll out on board sprinkled with powdered sugar. Spread with peanut butter, nuts and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and slice to desired thickness.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain. Layer macaroni, salt, pepper, margarine and cheese. Shake milk, egg and flour together. Pour on top of macaroni. Then put cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until milk is absorbed.

title: fried or grilled gator ribs
directions: Note:
If using older gator, use meat tenderizer; marinate overnight.
Cover ribs with water

title: hashed brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (do not cook potatoes first).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Scald milk; cool.
Melt shortening and add to scalded milk. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
When milk is cool, add flour, salt and sugar sifted together, a small amount at a time.
Stir well and add vanilla, beaten eggs and yeast before dough gets too stiff.
Knead well on a floured board.
Have a soft dough.

title: grilled merlot lamb(with herb mint sauce)
directions: Divide the lamb and place in two heavy-duty ziploc bags (the lamb will pull apart naturally in sections).
In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients except lamb and Herb Mint Sauce. Blend and pour combined ingredients over lamb.
Seal the bags and shake gently to allow marinade to coat lamb completely. Refrigerate at least 6 hours or up to 1 day, turning bags several times.
Grill the lamb over medium heat to desired doneness (medium rare is delicious with good lamb!).
After removing lamb from grill, let it rest and cool a bit so that its inner juices can thicken and not all be lost when it is sliced.
Slice and plate the lamb, drizzling the Herb Mint Sauce over it or serving it on the side.
Enjoy with garlic mashed potatoes or roasted potatoes or wild rice.

title: beef and cabbage casserole(the working woman's cabbage rolls)
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Drain and set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place with long points toward center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press on bottom and sides to form a crust, sealing perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower oven rack.
Crust will be puffy.
Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage mixture.
Bake on lower oven rack for 30 to 35 minutes. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: easy bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and raisins in a large bowl; pour water over cereal mixture and mix well. Cool. Combine next 4 ingredients; make a well in center of flour mixture. Add buttermilk, oil, eggs, pecans and bran mixture; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Cover and store in refrigerator as long as one week. When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling two-thirds full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: italian mashed potatoes - sartue
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Mash.
Add oleo, milk, Ricotta cheese and pepperoni.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes (just to heat through).
Bread crumbs may be sprinkled on top before baking.

title: two chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour, then pour in rest of ingredients. Cook until thick and then pour into baked pie shells. Use egg whites for topping. Brown topping.

title: 4 in one
directions: Repeat layers and cover with 1 quart of tomatoes.
Bake in tightly covered dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine flour, soda, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, buttermilk and margarine.
Slowly stir in dry ingredients. Batter will be thick.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of batter onto lightly greased griddle.

title: darlene drew's layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer first 7 ingredients in order given. Mix together salad dressing or mayonnaise and sugar. Pour on top of layered salad. Garnish with chopped tomato just before serving. (Tomato acid will break down the salad dressing mixture, so it is important to garnish just prior to serving or let individuals add tomatoes as desired.)

title: janet's meatball stew
directions: In a 4-quart pan, combine water, frozen meatballs, undrained beans, beef bouillon granules, onion, basil and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling.
Add spaghetti.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until meatballs are heated through.
Stir in drained mixed vegetables and undrained chopped or crushed tomatoes.
Heat.
Serve with Parmesan cheese or grated sharp cheese, Monterey Jack, Swiss or cheese of your choice.
Very good.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper to boil.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: delicious chocolate pie
directions: While browning pie crust; mix dry ingredients first; sugar, salt, cocoa and cornstarch.
Stir and smash up lumps.
Add milk and yolks and cook over medium heat until thick.
Then add butter and vanilla, mix with mixer and pour into baked pie crust.

title: winter relish
directions: Place sugar in a large refrigerator dish.
Grind all fruit and add to sugar and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for weeks in a refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add marshmallows.
Add strawberries, pineapple, apricots and bananas.
Stir.
Freeze in paper baking cups.

title: apple balls
directions: Combine sugar, water, cloves and lemon rind.
Cook for several minutes until syrupy.
Remove cloves and lemon rind.
Add apple balls (apples should be peeled and cut with a melon ball cutter). Add 1 or 2 drops food coloring.
Cook until apples are tender. Chill and serve with roasted meats or poultry.

title: fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from stove; add 1/2 cup marshmallow cream and 1 cup nuts, if desired.
When cold, cut in pieces.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss above ingredients and serve.

title: blueberry bars
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and graham cracker crumbs and pat down in bottom (and up around sides a little) of a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or Pyrex baking dish.
Set aside.
Beat thoroughly cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla and spread evenly in graham cracker crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Then spread with 1 can "Comstock blueberry pie filling.
Chill.
When chilled, cover with 1 (8 ounce) carton thawed Cool Whip.
Refrigerate, uncovered, until serving time.
Cut into 18 bars.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk. Beat 3 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip; stir well. Line 9 x 13 inch pan with graham crackers; cover with pudding mixture. Continue layering graham crackers and pudding mixture. Cover top of dessert with a layer of graham crackers. Add melted chocolate frosting to top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute broccoli, margarine and onion until tender.
Mix corn muffin mix, eggs and cottage cheese, then combine.
Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes or until golden brown. One cup grated Cheddar cheese may be added for a different flavor.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except salt and pepper.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with fish!
Makes 1 cup.

title: polish disasters
directions: Fry meat together.
Drain grease and add jar of Cheez Whiz. Simmer until cheese is melted.
Put on slices of party rye. Freeze on a cookie sheet.
When frozen, put in a plastic bag. When ready to eat, pop in oven for a few minutes until hot.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Cook all these ingredients until clear and slightly thickened. Slice apples after peeling.
Put in jars.
Cover with filling. Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Grate the carrots. Cut onion fine.
Stir all together and let stand for several hours to blend flavors.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together ingredients on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Blanch tomatoes in hot water and peel.
Wash peppers; peel onions and garlic.
Dice tomatoes; chop onions, peppers and garlic.
Mix all ingredients together and boil until thick (20 to 30 minutes).
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath 10 to 15 minutes.
(Best to wear rubber gloves when handling peppers.)

title: ribbon sandwich
directions: Shell and chop eggs.
Mix with 1/4 cup of mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Drain tuna; mix with 1/4 cup of mayonnaise, celery and sweet pickle.
Refrigerate in separate bowls.
Trim crusts from each loaf.
Slice each loaf into 5 to 7 horizontal slices.
Alternate spreading tuna and egg mixtures on each horizontal slice.
Wrap in foil or plastic and refrigerate overnight.
Cut this loaf of alternating bread and fillings into 15 to 20
crosswise slices.
Each slice can be halved.
Keep refrigerated until served.
Yields 10 servings.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into rolls. Let rise. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated beef and broccoli supper(sirloin steak is tenderized in a light ginger marinade)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt margarine until sizzling.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender (5 to 6 minutes).
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, stir together remaining ingredients except steak, tomatoes and rice.
Add sirloin strips; let stand 5
minutes.
Add sirloin and marinade to vegetable mixture.
Continue cooking and stirring occasionally, until meat is browned (6 to 8 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes and cover.
Let stand 2 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Serve meat and vegetables with juices over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings in 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and the Marshmallow Creme. Chill. Dip sliced apples in pineapple or lemon juice to keep fresh. Store in Ziploc bag until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, place dip in bowl.
Arrange apples, peeling side up, around dip.

title: honey crackle
directions: Into a large shallow roasting pan, turn the popped corn. Sprinkle the almonds over the corn.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Line muffin pan with large paper baking cups. Fill each one 2/3 full.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice
and
boil
carrots
in salted water until tender (don't cook
until
soft);
cool and alternate layers of carrots, onion and pepper.
Beat remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over
vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
May be prepared several days in advance.

title: hot dog cheese wrap
directions: Place bacon between 2 sheets of paper towels.
Cook on High for 2 minutes or until partially cooked.
Split buns and spread with mustard; set aside.
Cut cheese into 8 (1/4-inch) strips. Divide cheese into 2 stacks.
Cut each hot dog lengthwise in half (almost through).
Lay cheese strips in slit.
Wrap bacon strip around each hot dog.
Place hot dogs in buns.
Wrap each with paper towel.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.

title: crock-pot tuna salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup chips; stir well.
Pour into a greased crock-pot.
Top with reserved chips.
Cover and cook on low setting for 5 to 8 hours.
Makes 4 servings (2 quarts).

title: pizza puff
directions: In skillet, break up sausage; cook slowly, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, turning meat to cook evenly.
Drain well.
Place 4 slices of the bread in bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine tomato paste and basil; spread over bread in pan.
Place half of the cheese slices over bread.
Spoon all of the sausage over cheese; place remaining cheese slices over sausage.
Top with remaining bread slices, trimming crusts, if needed, to fit.

title: frosted delight bars
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Mix shortening, white sugar, vanilla and eggs until fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg white with salt until stiff.
Beat in brown sugar.
Spread on dough.
Top with nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut in squares or bars.

title: crystal garden
directions: Mix salt, water and ammonia together.
Pour mixture over several small pieces of charcoal in a small bowl.
Put several drops of colored inks on various parts of it and leave undisturbed for several days.
Crystals will form into interesting formations, growing and sprouting every day.
It will be white where no ink is used.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Note:
For variety, any other items that would be good on a pizza may be added to this casserole; such as, mushrooms, sausage, olives, green peppers, onion, etc.

title: boneless chicken breasts
directions: Melt stick of butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Flour chicken lightly and lay in butter.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, lemon pepper and paprika.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Turn and sprinkle with garlic salt, lemon pepper and paprika again and bake for 20 minutes.

title: ham devils
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks.
Add mayonnaise and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Stir in ham and all remaining ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg whites.

title: venison stew
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat in oil. In a large stew pot add seasonings, soup, wine, vegetables and meat. Cover and let simmer for no less than 8 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and flour.
Cream. Add crushed potato chips, chopped pecans, vanilla and water. Cream thoroughly.
Chill.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form cookies into balls.
Press onto cookie sheet. Bake.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Slice strawberries and mix with glaze; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
In large bowl, tear cake in pieces; pour cream cheese mixture over cake and pour glaze over all.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli slowly until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Pour oil in skillet.
Heat until hot and add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and stir until thick and add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over broccoli.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat, onions and seasonings together lightly;
put
in	a

title: lemon lace pudding
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks.
Cream the butter or margarine with the sugar.
Add grated rind and juice.
Blend into the first mixture the egg yolks, flour and milk.
Beat the 2 egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Place dish into pan of hot water in a 350° oven and bake 35 to 45 minutes, until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Stir 3 times while
baking.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, salsa, onions and garlic. Set aside.
Coat chicken with flour.
In a 10-inch skillet with cover, heat oil over medium heat; saute chicken for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian meat loaf pie
directions: Mix beef, 1/2 of tomatoes, oats, one Egg Beaters, Parmesan and seasonings.
Divide in half.
Pat half of meat mixture into sides and bottom of 10-inch pie plate.
Blend Ricotta, 1 Egg Beaters and garlic powder.
Spread into meat shell.
Pat remaining meat into a 10-inch circle on wax paper.
Place on top of pie.
Spread remaining tomatoes on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in wedges.

title: reece's cups
directions: Mix well until like dough.
Roll into small balls.
Have chocolate melted.
Pour chocolate into bottom of candy cup. Place peanut butter mixture in center.
Cover with chocolate.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread in large bowl or Dutch oven pot.
Add bread torn into small pieces.
Add onion, celery, sage, salt and pepper. Pour hot broth on top (enough to make mixture very moist and wet).
Completely saturate.
Use potato masher and mash well. Cover with a lid.
Let steam 15 minutes.
Mash again.
Put in baking pan and bake at 400° approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Sift or mix well the flour and sugar.
Add egg and mix thoroughly with a fork.
Pour the can of apples in baking dish or pie plate and sprinkle cinnamon to taste on the apples.
Sprinkle the moist flour mixture evenly over the apples.
Dot with butter. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Stir in taco seasoning and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix taco sauce and salad dressing together. Combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients except tortilla chips.
Right before serving, add sauce mixture and tortilla chips.
Makes 12 servings.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight, preferably, covered with water one-inch above bean level.
Brown sausage and cut bacon into 1-inch squares and brown with sausage.
Add celery, carrots and onions, all diced.
Crush or chop garlic and add with pepper to taste and saute with vegetables until tender.
Add beans to pot.
Cook forever, until beans break up into a gooey mess.
Add stock and supplement with water as needed.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter.
Spread in greased pan.
Press down lightly.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325°.
Optional:
Put favorite pie filing in between layers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well; put in well greased casserole.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix whipped topping, cream cheese, and pudding together. Pour mixture into piecrust and garnish with grated chocolate or chocolate pieces. Chill for 30 minutes and serve.

title: wudge(peanut butter fudge)
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: apple pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix together and place in pie shell.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top.
Add 3 tablespoons water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken (pork chops) with brown rice
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add onion and rice.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place this mixture in casserole dish and add beef broth, mushrooms and salt.
Wash and salt and pepper chicken.
Place chicken in casserole dish on top of rice mixture. Bake, covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and zesty spareribs
directions: Place pork spareribs, meaty sides up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, in 325° oven 1 1/2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients; brush over pork.
Roast, turning and brushing frequently with pineapple mixture until pork is done, about 45 minutes longer. (Use about half of the pineapple mixture to brush pork.)
Heat remaining pineapple mixture to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve with pork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blender pancakes
directions: Put milk, eggs and oil in blender; blend.
Add flour and blend.
Add sugar and blend.
Add baking powder and blend.
Yield: 10 to 13 pancakes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Let stand overnight in salted water. Cook in same water until almost tender.
Drain off all water. Saute onions, pepper and celery in the 1/2 cup oleo.
Mix eggplant, bread crumbs, sauteed vegetables, beaten eggs, salt, if needed, small amount of sage (1/2 teaspoon) and chopped pimento. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350°
in buttered casserole until slightly browned.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Mix well 1/4 cup gravy with beef, bread cubes, egg, onion, salt and dash of pepper. Shape firmly into loaf pan (7 x 3-inch), cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven, check to see if done, drain.
Separate rolls, place crosswise over top and down sides of loaf overlapping slightly.
Bake 15 minutes more. Heat remaining gravy.
Serve with loaf.

title: taco dip
directions: Put refried beans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook hamburger and follow directions on back of taco seasoning mix packet.
Let hamburger mixture cool.
Mix sour cream and 1/2 jar taco sauce together.
Put on top of cooled hamburger.
Put diced tomato, shredded lettuce and taco cheese on top and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Use chips for dipping.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables and sugar in bowl; stir well.
Combine Italian dressing, dry mustard and celery seed in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour mixture over vegetables, tossing to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled. Stir and serve using a slotted spoon.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and blueberries.
Add water to juices, making 3 1/2 cups.
Heat to boiling point.
Dissolve jello in hot water and juices.
Cool until partly congealed.
Add fruits, nuts and the marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm. Serves 24.

title: pa apps' spaghetti sauce(from medina high's class of '69)
directions: Mix all ingredients in 8-quart kettle and throughout, stir. Heat on medium heat.
Let cook in slow boil for 1/2 to 3/4 hour. After cooled, put in containers and freeze.
When reheating, use low to medium heat so not to burn.
Makes 1 3/4 gallons of sauce.

title: chip or vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine all ingredients.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Add the lime jello (dry) and mix well.

title: banana liqueur
directions: Mash the bananas and add the vanilla and cooled simple syrup to the vodka.
Shake gently.
Steep at least 1 week.
Strain and filter.
It can be enjoyed now, but if left for 2 or 3 months it will have a richer flavor.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Cut center out of biscuits.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown, turning once.
Shake doughnut in sugar and cinnamon until covered.
Serve while warm.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie plate; beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour in pie plate; bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and orange rind.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add dates, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Mix well and add buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in a large well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and mix 1/2 cup orange juice with 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Pour over the cooled cake.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add 2 cups flour, then soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add remaining flour.
Drop tablespoonfuls of dough onto cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of flat bottomed glass.
Dip in sugar and flatten cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.
Makes approximately 50 cookies.

title: basil cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place rolls, cut sides up, on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Spread margarine on rolls; top with cheese and basil.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot n' squash casserole
directions: Place crackers in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine cheese, soup, eggs and butter; stir in squash, carrots and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into baking dish; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick tuna or chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add flour and salt to mixture.
Mix well.
Add mashed bananas.
Add soda to sour milk and stir.
Add milk to mixture; stir well.
Add nuts.
Pour mixture into well-greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 275° to 300° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: energy bars
directions: Toast Quaker oats in pan.
Add in Rice Krispies, peanuts and raisins after taken off heat.
Melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows in pot and add to mixture.
Mix well and turn onto sheet; cool and cut.

title: cauliflower-garlic soup
directions: Simmer garlic in stock in a covered pot 20 minutes.
Add cauliflower, salt and pepper and simmer another 30 minutes until vegetables are very tender.
Cool.
Puree in blender in batches and return to the stock pot.
Stir in half and half.
Taste and correct seasonings, if necessary.
Simmer to serving temperature. Top each serving with a sprinkling of nutmeg.
Serves 6.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender but firm.
Drain and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish (ungreased). Add pimentos, onion, garlic and onion salt; toss gently.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place the bread cubes on top and pour butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is toasted.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup coconut, 2 cups milk and the cornstarch in blender and blend until mixed.
Pour into saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add remaining coconut and vanilla.
Allow to cool completely.
Prepare topping and spread on top of filling. Add toasted coconut and refrigerate.

title: cheddar potato slices
directions: Mix soup, paprika and pepper.
In greased 2 qt shallow dish arrange potatoes in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle with cheese. Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover and bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.
If desired, garnish with fresh parsley.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let chill 20 minutes.
Serve with fried or boiled shrimp.

title: easy tomato-pepper relish
directions: Place chopped tomatoes in a colander for 30 minutes to drain off juices.
In a bowl combine tomatoes and green peppers; add salad dressing.
Cover; chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: quick and easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save the broth.
Cut or tear the flour tortillas and drop them in the boiling chicken broth.
Add chicken, then let it simmer.
Will be ready in 15 minutes.
Never fails!

title: pickled peach salad
directions: Chop pickled peaches, removing pits.
Reserve 1 cup juice. Dissolve jello in boiling water; add chopped peaches, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into serving dish and chill until set.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large pot, add oil and brown meat and onion.
When browned, cover with boiling water, about 5 cups.
Add salt and pepper and simmer until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour, add carrots.
Peel and boil potatoes.
When carrots are cooked, remove meat and carrots to large baking dish.
Thicken broth with flour, smoothly blended with 1/3 cup water.
Stir until gravy boils and taste for more seasoning.
Pour gravy over meat and carrots.
Drain potatoes.
Mash with butter and milk and pile on top of stew.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine enchilada sauce and soup in saucepan; warm slightly.
Dip tortillas in sauce, breaking in half as needed to fit, and making layers in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer tortillas, hamburger and cheese.
Continue, ending with cheese.

title: lorraine's spice loaf
directions: Boil raisins for 5 mins. with cover on.
Add together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add raisins, oil, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: Bring chicken to a boil.
Cook until tender; drain water from chicken.
Stir in cream of chicken and broccoli soup.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serves 6.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: green bean soup(german)
directions: In a stockpot peel potatoes, and cut into bite size pieces. Bring potatoes to a boil. Cut bacon and onion into tiny pieces. Add to separate skillet, simmer until bacon is pretty done and onions are clear. Remove bacon and onions, leaving liquid.
Add flour (more or less depending on how thick you want soup to be), making a roux.
When potatoes are done, add roux and chicken paste or bouillon cubes, and green beans to stockpot of boiling potatoes.
Season with small amount of Maggi and/or salt and pepper.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In casserole dish, combine sugar and flour.
Pour in pineapple with juice; cover with cheese.
Cover with crackers and butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion; drain. In large mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients (except grated cheese). Mix well and add meat mixture to soup/Tot mixture. Put in casserole dish and bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes. In the last 5 to 10 minutes, pull out and add cheese to top; put back in oven.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
While cake is still hot, punch holes over the top with fork.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over cake.
Heat cherry pie filling and add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon almond extract.
Mix well and cover cake while still hot.
Cake needs to set a few hours before serving.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.
Roll and drop by tablespoon on hot nonstick griddle or frypan until golden brown.
Makes 30 small cakes.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain fat off beef.
Combine all ingredients.
Use best judgment when adding spices.
Boil a few minutes.
Turn down heat.
Simmer an hour or as long as possible.

title: french pickles
directions: Cook each vegetable separately until vegetables are barely tender.
Season to taste with salt.
Drain well.
Add mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with vinegar and let come to boiling point, stirring frequently.
Pack into jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: cheryl's baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop onto ungreased baking sheet or pan. Bake at 450° for 10-12 minutes.

title: dannon apple spice cake
directions: Combine and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beverly's swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients and form into 8 large balls.
Cover with 3/4 cup catsup and 3/4 cup water (mixed).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and melt in a 350° oven.
Mix dry ingredients and milk.
Remove pan from oven and pour mixture over melted oleo.
Add peaches and bake 1 hour.
(Do not stir peaches in mixture, just pour from can around sides and middle.)

title: homemade brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl on High for 2 minutes or until mixture is completely melted.
Stir in sugar until well blended.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended and stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind squash, hot and sweet peppers and onions.
Mix in salt. Put a tray of ice cubes on top; let set for 1 hour.
Mix rest of ingredients together; add to squash mixture.
Bring to boil and seal in jars.

title: apple-onion-prune skillet
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet; add onions and saute, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Add apples, prunes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for about 5 minutes or until apples and onions are tender.
Serve hot with sausage, roast pork, pork chops or ham.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pierogi-borscht
directions: Make stock with soup bone and soup meat.
Season as desired. Add red beets, sour cream and vinegar to warm stock so cream does not curdle.
Mix egg with flour, salt and water to the consistency of dough ball that can be rolled out thin.
Roll, cut in 3-inch squares and cover with a tea towel.

title: rapidrise bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, the yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl. Heat water, milk and margarine to 125° to 130°; stir into flour mixture.
Stir in egg.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Sprinkle a clean surface with flour; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet and shape dough into a round loaf; place on sheet.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes.
While warm, poke holes in entire top of cake with fork.
Mix 2 cups powdered sugar and 1 small can lemonade together and pour over top of cake.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Let cake cool and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan (or you can do like I did and put it in a regular pie plate).

title: cinnamon buns(basic sweet dough)
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat, heat milk, water and butter to 120° to 130° (very warm).
With mixer at low speed, gradually pour liquid into dry ingredients.
Increase speed and beat in eggs and 2 cups of flour.
Gradually stir in enough flour (4 1/4 cups approximately) to make soft dough.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic (10 minutes approximately).
Shape dough into ball and place in large, greased bowl, turning over so top is greased. Cover with towel and let rise until doubled (1 hour).
Punch down dough and divide into number of baking pans you wish to use.
Cover dough with towel for 15 minutes.

title: stick kringle
directions: Mix margarine, flour and salt as for pie crust.
Add sour cream.
Make ball with dough.
Divide ball in four.
Roll each quarter to measure 10 x 16-inches.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While still hot, drizzle with 1 tablespoon butter, milk and powdered sugar to make frosting smooth enough to drizzle over each stick.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, mix pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Dump dry cake mix over mixture.
Cover with ground pecans or nuts.
Slice butter thinly and place on top of nuts.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: delta's jello salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in saucepan; bring to a "good" boil.
Add water.
Put in large bowl.
Put in refrigerator until semi-jelled.
Remove from refrigerator and fold in remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator until jelled.
Makes a large dish.
Good for "covered dish" item or holidays.

title: cole slaw
directions: In a small pot, heat the water, vinegar and the butter.
Mix together the sugar, mustard, salt and flour.
After mixing, add to it 1 well beaten egg.
Mix well and then pour into pot of water and vinegar.
Keep stirring to keep smooth.
When thickened, pour over grated cabbage.
Store in the refrigerator.
Will keep for days.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer canned tomatoes and chicken stock until liquid is reduced by one-half.
Season with chopped parsley, onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil and thyme.

title: turnips with corn dodgers
directions: Cook turnips with pork in 2 quarts water.
Cook until meat and turnips are good and tender.
Mix cornmeal.
Let it be where you can pat out in round patties.
Drop in boiling turnips; do not stir.
Just push around with spoon.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soups, milk, chilies, onion and chicken.
Fill pan by layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: candy date roll
directions: Cook together first 5 ingredients until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add margarine and pecans.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour into a mound of powdered sugar and knead until a roll can be formed.
Roll in waxed paper.
Slice when hardened.

title: stuffed quahogs
directions: In large skillet, saute onions with 1/4 butter until onions are soft.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and oregano.
Add minced quahogs and rest of butter.
As butter melts, blend quahogs and onions.
Stir frequently until butter melts and mixture is heated through.
Remove from heat and add bread crumbs until a dry but pasty consistency is achieved.
Stuff shells with the mixture and bake in a 350° oven until browned.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: broccoli and cheese tidbits
directions: Cook broccoli to thaw in salty water.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish.
Cover with crushed Cheese Tid-Bits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't let Cheese Tid-Bits get dark.

title: barbecue brisket(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Place meat in baking dish; pour over the liquid smoke. Sprinkle meat with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt to tenderize.
Cover tightly and let stand in refrigerator overnight. The next morning, sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Leaving meat in the liquid smoke, cover the dish with foil and place in a 275° oven.
(Tuck foil around edge of dish, but not around meat.)
Bake 5 hours, then uncover.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and continue baking for 1 more hour without cover.
Remove meat from dish and cool to slice.
